@{b}Season Four Episodes@{ub}

Buffy-mania began to show signs of dropping off around the time of the US airing of season 4, the hubbub slowed down and people viewed the show as a Serious Thing, not just a Next Big Thing. Whether or not the quality of this season had anything to do with that is debatable, but the fact remains this season was very awkward, especially for long-time fans. Buffy goes to college (neat Descendents reference there), Angel's gone, everythings all over the place! The Initiative proves interesting to those of us who thought "but hang on, if Giles can fight a vampire, surely the army could tackle them?"

