@{b}Season Five Episodes@{ub}

Buffy's fifth season is easily its darkest yet. Some enjoyable diversions aside - see The Replacement - this season sees the death of Buffy's mother Joyce, and tackles issues such as self-harm and depression in a way that previous seasons really only touched upon - it's almost like a nightmarish document on the human condition. Add the sudden, inexplicable presence of Dawn and you've got a unique new perspective on this battle between good and evil.

