@node "ABOUTGUIDE" "Buffy.guide: About"

@{b}About Buffy.guide@{ub}

Hey guys... it's been so long I've forgotten how to upload to Aminet! :O) If you still give a shit about this, e-mail me! By way of explanation for my absence, some really nasty shit happened to me last year, plus I left college so my internet access is extremely limited: 15 minutes at the library now and then, which is only up the road now since I @{i}moved out!! @{ui} No more stepdad anymore. Another change is that now I'm using UAE... Miggy's right by my side but I can't afford a gfx card, so UAE & P96 is way faster at the moment, plus my Miggy's RMB is broke :O( It's funny how a PC, sitting idle, crashes sometimes. And AmigaOS runs faster under emulation on x86 than "native" Windows. I also gave up the cider drinking :O) My friend I used to drink with, he's a speed-freak now, so whatever. I had to get away from that fucker.

I'm not sure about the fate of the HTML version... It always looked way nicer than the guide but was much less functional, and I have other things to do like write songs and paint than wade through the most disgusting hypertext ever written. The guide was already a mess by the time of the last release - I had kept on top of the new episodes but neglected areas like character info, so to get it in shape I've probably spent 80 hours... Partly because for season five and six, I've been writing my own outlines. I really don't know why, since it would be quicker to copy them off the Buffy site. Some of the new outlines just lack warmth, they're no fun to read. It takes me at least 100 mins to write one synopsis, sitting here next to the VCR. The outlines I didn't write have still been edited, to clarify some points or to add details. Some mistakes may remain, but they're fixed on discovery.


@{b}How to use this guide@{ub}

Buffy The Vampire Slayer Guide is designed for the AmigaGuide© system. If you aren't familiar with AmigaGuide, try clicking on the Help button at the top of the AmigaGuide window.

There are several ways of navigating around this guide:

@{u}Browsing through the main page@{uu}
The main page has a list of all the Buffy episodes that I currently have information on. Click on the links to read outlines and comments for your chosen episode. @{"Click here" LINK "MAIN"} to go to the main page.

@{u}Using the browse buttons@{uu}
All the episode nodes are in the correct order, so you can read the whole Buffy story from start to finish by using the Browse buttons. Character info nodes are also in alphabetical order.

@{u}Using the index@{uu}
I've supplied an @{"index" LINK "BUFFYINDEX"} for the episode names, so you can search for episodes alphabetically. This can also be accessed at any time using the index button at the top of the AmigaGuide window.

@{u}Using a string search@{uu}
Matthew Fletcher's BuffyGuideSearch tool is included in the archive, which Buffy.guide requires to execute a string search. Click on the @{"String Search" SYSTEM "newcli WINDOW=CON:20/20/400//Buffy from Buffy.guide.cli"} button to start a new search, or on the @{"?" LINK "SEARCHREADME"} button to view Matthew's readme. You should @{b}never@{ub} rename Buffy.guide, because the search tool won't be able to find it. If you have problems using the search, see the troubleshooting section below.

@{u}Using the Major Buffy Events list@{uu}
This is a chronological list of all the events of particular significance in the Buffy story, eg. Angel's first kiss with Buffy. @{"Click here" LINK "EVENTS"} to check it out.


@{b}Other information available in the guide@{ub}

@{u}Character Profiles@{uu}
A collection of profiles, odd articles, etc., on the characters (heroes, villains and otherwise) in Buffy and their corresponding actors. Character Profiles also now includes all the guys from the old Death Row section - I figured if you're looking for a character by name you may not know which side they're on, plus some of them are ambiguous, Spike for instance. @{"Click here" LINK "CHARACTERPROFILES"} to view the Character Profiles page.

@{u}Vamp Vocabulary@{uu}
A Slayer-Speak glossary. Handy if you want to sound like one of the Scooby gang. Accessible via the @{"Main page" LINK "MAIN"}, or @{"click here" LINK "VAMPVOC"} to go to the Vamp Vocab page.

@{u}Buffy Marathon@{uu}
An insane experiment in the immersive experience of Buffywatching. Not one of those scary stalker things, @{"here" LINK "BUFFYMARATHON"} I talk about watching the entire existing backlog of Buffy episodes in one sitting - breaking only to pee - to see if it drives me insane.


@{b}Problems with the guide@{ub}

I cannot possibly test Buffy.guide on every configuration. Although it works great on my Amiga, here is a quick run-down of the problems you could face:

@{b}Problem:@{ub}  The buttons etc. aren't lined up properly
@{b}Solution:@{ub}  You need XHelvetica.font/11 on your system. This is part of the MagicWB package, so I assumed most people have access to that font. If it's not there, AmigaGuide® will fall back to your system default text, which will be fixed-width and mess up the tabs. You can try changing the font tag on line 5 using a text-editor.

@{b}Problem:@{ub}  The search button won't work!
@{b}Solution:@{ub}  Check that:
1.    The files BuffyGuideSearch, Buffy.guide.cli and Buffy.guide.search are in the BuffyGuide drawer
2.    You have MultiView (or a replacement with the same name) installed on your system
3.    You have a 68020 or better processor!
4.    The protection flags of BuffyGuideSearch are set to RWED (default)
5.    You are using the AmigaGuide system to view the guide, as opposed to WinGuide on a PC, which obviously cannot run AmigaOS programs like the search tool
6.    NewCLI is in your path, or in ROM (OS2+). This is the least likely to cause problems.

@{b}Problem:@{ub}  Sometimes depending on the size of the AmigaGuide® window, links dissappear and are replaced by strange symbols!
@{b}Solution:@{ub}  It has happened to me once or twice. A bug in AmigaGuide®, which I, of course, cannot fix! You may also notice that web URLs aren't correctly wrapped, for a similar reason - it's just the way that AmigaGuide® handles wrapping (ie. badly).

@{b}Problem:@{ub}  There's a broken link in your guide!
@{b}Solution:@{ub}  Contact me and I'll fix it (give as much info as possible). I do have a links checker so this shouldn't happen, but it's possible that a link takes you to the wrong page, so keep an eye out for that...

@{b}Problem:@{ub}  The guide looks weird when I view it on Winguide on the PC, or an old version of AmigaGuide®. I also find I can't use the search facility.
@{b}Solution:@{ub}  Winguide has no support for system commands or for wordwrap. Both of these facilities are required to view BuffyGuide at its best. All I can say is that if you give the author some feedback they might be motivated into adding wordwrap... Just use UAE if you really must view it on a PC.


@{b}FAQ@{ub}

@{b}Q:@{ub}  Buffy the what...?
@{b}A:@{ub}  Maybe you're in the wrong place, dude! Well if you're new to the series then you should be able to learn a lot from this guide. Start at the beginning, and read through to the end, I guess...

@{b}Q:@{ub}  Why do you need version numbers for an episode guide?!
@{b}A:@{ub}  The main purpose of the version numbers is so you know whether of not you have the latest version of the guide. I know it seems a little daft, but as a measure of how Buffy.guide has evolved, it works. I won't pretend I know the first thing about version numbers :O)

@{b}Q:@{ub}  Where can I find information on what might happen in the future of Buffy?
@{b}A:@{ub}  Visit @{u}www.buffyslayer.com@{uu}, go to the postings board and there's usually someone around there looking in a big crystal ball. Or probably talking to their aunt Mildred who works in the make-up department...

@{b}Q:@{ub}  How can I help you with the Buffy guide?
@{b}A:@{ub}  Thanks for asking. I need someone to tell me how to link to individual sections of an AmigaGuide node when line numbers don't work because it's driving me insane. Also does anyone know how to wordwrap in FrexxEd? Any incorrect information that you spot in the guide, I'd like you to email me about. Don't just think everyone else will because unfortunatly then no-one does. If you are my best friend ever, you will send any of this info to @{u}chris.sheffeild@talk21.com@{uu} !!

@{b}Q:@{ub}  How do I install Buffy.guide?
@{b}A:@{ub}  Buffy.guide is best kept with all it components, in a drawer called BuffyGuide, which can be kept wherever you like. When you unpack BuffyGuide.lha, LhA should create a drawer called BuffyGuide, and you should be able to drag this drawer wherever you like.

@{b}Q:@{ub}  Are you a Buffy expert?
@{b}A:@{ub}  No way! The only Buffy expert is Joss, man.

@{b}Q:@{ub}  Are you infringing copyright by making an AmigaGuide® of this information?
@{b}A:@{ub}  I sure hope not. There's an X-Files guide doing the rounds and as far as I know there have been no objections to that. As for using other people's episode descriptions... Well, I included all the credits that were on the web (unlike the author of certain other guides, no names mentioned!) so I don't see any problem. Besides, I'm promoting Buffy :-)

@{b}Q:@{ub}  How do I write to one of the stars?
@{b}A:@{ub}  Their Name, c/o Buffy the Vampire Slayer, c/o The Warner Brothers Television Network, 4000 Warner Blvd., Burbank, CA 91522

@{b}Q:@{ub}  Can I link to the Buffy website? How?
@{b}A:@{ub}  Use this code to link, using the button on the Buffy server:

@{fg shine}<a href="http://www.buffy.com"><img src="http://www.buffy.com/bronze/buffybanner.gif" width="468" height="60" alt="Visit The Buffy the Vampire Slayer Official Web Site" border=1 ></a>@{fg text}

@{b}Q:@{ub}  Who are the people who post at the Buffy website who seem to be connected to the show?
@{b}A:@{ub}	@{u}Screen Name@{uu}			@{u}Identity@{uu}

	joss				Joss Whedon - Creator of Buffy
	Ty King				Ty King - writer
	Jeff Pruitt			Jeff Pruitt - stunt coordinator
	RD				Secret guy from David Greenwalt's office
	Seth Green			Seth Green (Oz) - actor
	Alyson (Willow)			Alyson Hannigan - actress
	Apollo - Buffy Web Support Team	Webmaster of the site
	Erika Amato (Velvet Chain)		Lead singer of a band appearing in Buffy
	SCOUT				Secret person from the show

I don't know who the secret people are... I've never personally seen any of them post either.

@{b}Q:@{ub}  I don't like all the American spellings. You should correct them to real English.
@{b}A:@{ub}  Cue my old left-wing English student rant: Oh, "Real" English?! Why is 'Colour' any more correct than 'Color'? Spelling is entirely arbitrary (look at the word Knight and then try telling me you pronounce it exactly as it's spelt!) and therefore not worth arguing about. Plus it's an American show, for crying out loud!

@{b}Q:@{ub}  That's a weird attitude, since you're an ex-English language student!
@{b}A:@{ub}  As a linguist, I describe; I do not prescribe. Dude. But don't worry, English spellings like "mum" and "arse" will appear in the bits I write. Because I am from England!


