@node "BUFFYVSDRACULA" "Buffy.guide: Buffy vs. Dracula"

@{b}Buffy Vs. Dracula@{ub}
5ABB01

"You think you know... what you are, what's to come. You haven't even begun..." - Dracula

Apparently having trouble sleeping, our Slayer tosses and turns next to Riley. As if to quench some thirst, she creeps out to patrol and is soon chasing a vamp through the graveyard. Using a tombstone as a platform to leap from, she lands on the hapless creature and soon he's dust. Now able to sleep, Buffy climbs back into bed.

Next morning, the gang are enjoying a sunny day at the beach. Xander, Willow, Anya and Tara look on as Buffy and Riley play an aggressive game of football. Buffy bursts the football and they mess around in the sea before joining the rest of the guys and demanding burgers, but Xander unfortunately has so far failed to light the barbeque. Willow works some mojo to get the flame going and is just explaining that you must balance the elements carefully when a thunderstorm breaks out above them. Later on, a delivery truck arrives outside a castle-like building across town. Two guys jump out to load off a large crate and one of them drops it, spilling soil on the ground... Just then someone punches through the box with unfeasible strength, slashes at one guy's throat and gets away. Over at Giles' place, Willow fixes a problem with Giles' computer and he in turn informs her of his plans to move back to England and asks her not to tell anyone else. Willow is upset for Buffy, but also for herself and the rest of the gang - Giles has been like a father to them all for years. He seems confident that Buffy will understand.

Buffy has the strong urge to patrol again and can't get away from her mother's house fast enough, even turning down ice cream for a bit of slayage. At the graveyard however, Buffy is given a hard time by a vamp but eventually wins him over. Then a voice comes out from the dark commending her on her strength - someone, a vampire claiming to be Dracula himself, has been watching her. Meanwhile, Willow's conscience regarding Giles' secret is driving her crazy and she attempts to confess it to Xander as they look for Buffy.

Dracula attempts to charm Buffy by telling her that she is known around the world and that he came all the way to Sunnydale to meet her. She's not all that impressed, however, and attempts to stake him but he disappears into thin air just as Xander and Willow approach, reappearing behind them once Buffy has warned them away. Dracula bids them farewell, transforms himself into a bat and makes for the night sky. Back at Giles' house, Xander, Riley and Tara get increasingly jealous as Anya, Buffy and Willow talk about how sexy Dracula is! The girls insist they shouldn't go after Dracula straight away, so Giles checks the library while Willow researches on the internet for information on the Dark Prince...

As Xander and Anya walk home, they are followed by a husky dog (or a wolf or something, I dunno :O). They part ways and Dracula confronts Xander once he is alone, and makes him a servant. Dracula calls Xander "strange and off-putting" before dismissing him. Riley in his search for information, goes to Spike who tells him that he and Dracula are old rivals. Spike tells Riley that he's out of his depth and won't be able to find Dracula in time.

"You are magnificent," Dracula tells Buffy, standing in her room, at the foot of her bed. He commands her to pull the hair back from her neck. He moves closer and soon he drinks from her. Buffy wears a scarf round her neck to the Scooby meeting next morning, and denies being under his thrall. Xander eats a spider while the other guys are looking the other way. Riley follows Buffy outside and takes her scarf. Xander, Giles and Willow come out and see what Riley has seen. Xander, also under the thrall of Dracula, feigns scepticism. And eats a fly. Buffy assures Riley that she's his girl and the group make plans to keep Buffy safe at Xander's place while Willow and Tara work on a protection spell to stop Dracula returning to Buffy's house.

Giles and Riley hunt for Dracula while Xander and Anya watch over Buffy. Xander locks Anya in a cupboard and announces to Buffy: "I'm supposed to lead you to the Master now. There's this whole deal where I get to be immortal. You cool with that?" Dracula dismisses Xander as soon as he delivers Buffy, who soon realises she is powerless against the Count as long as she is charmed by him. Riley and Giles find the castle and split up, Riley eventually coming across Xander and knocking him out when he refuses to let him pass. Meanwhile, Giles steps through a door and falls 20 feet to the floor below. The Three Sisters appear and tickle and tease him, kissing him.

Dracula opens up his wrist and offers his blood to Buffy. Buffy refuses it, saying she is not hungry, and it may turn her into a vampire. But she is not close enough to death to become a vampire - he convinces her and she drinks from him. She finishes and throws Dracula across the room. The pair fight while Riley "rescues" a reluctant Giles from the sisters. Dracula vanishes, and as soon as she can see where he is about to re-appear, Buffy takes her stake and drives it into him as soon as he is visible. In come Riley, Giles and Xander, who is more than a tad annoyed about having been turned into a "spider-eating man-bitch". The guys leave the room, leaving Dracula to re-appear - only to be staked again by Buffy. "I'm standing right here!"

Back at Giles' house, Giles spoils Buffy with cookies in preparation for telling her about his plans to leave for England. Buffy says she also has something to tell him - Giles allows her to speak first. Buffy's eyes have been opened by the calling of the First Slayer, by her experiences with Dracula and darkness he saw in her power. She wants to learn more about where she comes from and wants to harness those aspects to become stronger. But she can't do it without Giles. "I need you to be my Watcher again." Giles doesn't mention moving to England - he's decided not to. For now.

Later, Buffy's getting ready to see a movie with Riley and is saying bye to her mum when she comes face to face with a slightly younger girl. "What are you doing here?" she asks her sister. Joyce calls through and suggests Buffy takes her sister to the movie too.

@{b}Notes@{ub}

In a way, the fact that they finally did an episode featuring Dracula himself is disappointing. I always got the feeling that the absense of any such plot was a case of the producers and writers trying to avoid the vampire cliches. Of course the show does revolve around some of the old cliches (mirrors, stakes, sunlight) but the show generally holds you in its fantasy world until the episode is over. This one brings you out of that illusion because the myth (?) of Dracula is so "real-world" and well-known that it reminds you this stuff isn't real. Which is sort of unpleasant.

Xander is funny as ever though and of course we have the all-impportant new arrival: Dawn, Buffy's sister.

Dracula's "You think you know what you are" line mirrors Tara's voice at the end of @{"Restless" LINK "RESTLESS"}.

@{b}Trivia@{ub}

Sarah's symbols: Whilst Sarah Michelle Gellar sports two tattos - the Chinese symbol for integrity on her back and a heart & dagger on her ankle - she seems to have gained another on her right shoulder during the beach scenes.

Dracula, Rudolph Martin played Sarah Michelle Gellar's onscreen lover in the daytime soap All My Children. Martin had another crack at Drac when he played Vlad the Impaler in the TV movie Dark Prince: The True Story of Dracula soon after appearing in Buffy.

He also looks worryingly like Changing Rooms' Laurence Llewelyn-Bowen.

Counting the similarities: Marti Noxon's script incorporates many elements from Bram Stoker's original Dracula novel. The possessed Xander is based on the book's bug-munching Renfield and the three sisters who ravish a willing Giles are Stoker's creations too. Wolves and bats feature heavily in the Dracula mythology too. The name Dracula means "Son of the Devil", by the way...

