@endnode

@node "REALME" "Buffy.guide: Real Me"

@{b}Real Me@{ub}
5ABB02

"There is nothing but you. You are the centre. And within you, there is the core of your being. Of what you are. Find it, breathe into it. Focus inward, let the world fall away... Fall away..."

Buffy and Giles are training. Buffy's training technique has taken on a more spiritual methodology recently and Buffy is using power from precious stones to balance upside-down on one arm on a large wooden stake... Until her sister knocks them over and Buffy falls to the floor. Time to go... At home, Buffy's sister writes in her diary: "Nobody knows who I am. Not the Real Me. It's like nobody cares enough to find out. I mean, does anybody ever ask me what I want to do with my life? Or what my opinion is on stuff? Or what restaurant to order in from? @{b}NO!!!@{ub} No-one understands. No-one has an older sister who's the Slayer..."

At breakfast, Buffy discovers her sister has put the last of the milk on her cereal. Joyce asks Buffy what her plans are for the day (a visit to the magic shop for training session supplies) and then suggests she take Dawn shopping for school equipment for the start of term, since she has work to do at the gallery. Dawn looks up from her breakfast, aghast. The three are still bickering when Riley knocks on the door. Buffy invited him over today but forgot - and has now made other plans. Giles, Buffy and Dawn ride in Giles' new BMW, and happen across Willow and Tara. Giles parks up and the five set off towards the magic shop - which they find closed... the owner dead inside. Buffy quickly sends Tara to wait outside where she is approached by a man who rambles incoherrently at her, telling her she doesn't belong here. Tara comes out of the shop to find Dawn sitting alone, looking withdrawn. They thumb-wrestle to pass the time until the others have finished.

Inside, the Scoobies suspect a vampire gang, and items from the inventory are also missing. Giles says books that were taken might reveal the Slayer's weaknesses, then trails off when he sees the profit margins for the shop. He wanders off, suddenly quite taken by the idea of being a magic shop proprietor, and notices a tacky unicorn statue has also gone missing. Menwhile underground, Harmony is brought a unicorn among other gifts from her minions - the vampire gang responsible for the magic shop raid. The group have a plan to kill the Slayer later tonight.

At home, Buffy and her mum argue over who will look after Dawn. Joyce needs to go to the gallery, Buffy has plans to go out with Riley and doesn't want to let him down again. When Buffy suggests Xander baby-sits, Dawn (who has a crush on Xander) is happy and it looks like they have their solution. Xander comes round and everything seems ok... until Dawn realises Anya is here too. Later, Willow and Tara talk about Dawn feeling like an outsider from the Scooby Gang; Tara says she feels like an outsider too. Willow tells Tara she isn't, that she has been accepted, and suggests all members wear a ring to identify each other. Tara says something like that would be good for Dawn.

Riley and Buffy patrol and discuss the tensions between Buffy and Dawn - Buffy feels like Dawn gets her own way. Xander meanwhile is finding out Dawn thinks the same way about Buffy over a board game. A brick comes throught the window with a note attached, addressed to Buffy: "Come out and die." The guys hear Harmony call from outside, and they go to the door, standing safe inside while Xander exchanges insults with Harmony and her minions. Unfortunately Dawn leaps to Xander's defence: "Oh yeah?! Come inside and say that!!" ... Oops. Harmony lunges in at Xander and pins him to the ground, much stronger than she was before. Anya tries to hit her with a lamp but she jumps up to hit her out of the way and Xander, taking his chance, kicks Harmony straight out the front foor, knocking her lackeys over like they were bowling pins.

Later, Buffy laughs at the idea that Harmony has minions until she finds out Dawn invited her in and goes upstairs to have some stern words. Meanwhile, Harmony and her gang walk back towards the lair when they come across Spike. Spike taunts Harmony and belittles her plans. She promises Buffy will be dead by sunrise. Back at Buffy's, Xander Riley and Buffy get weapons together. While Dawn listens from outside, undetected, Buffy says that by letting her get away with slip-ups like inviting Harmony in, they're turning her into a "stupid little idiot" who will get them all killed. Dawn storms out of the house and Anya follows her out to bring her back in. As Anya tries to force Dawn back into the house, Harmony's minions appear, knock Anya out and take off with Dawn. When Buffy learns that Dawn has been kidnapped she runs out, leaving Riley and Xander to tend to Anya.

At her lair, Harmony congratulates her "minionators" and goes over the plan to use Dawn as bait to lure Buffy into a trap and kill her. Buffy meanwhile arrives at Spike's crypt and beats the location of Harmony's cave out of him. Harmony is busy spilling her guts to Dawn about the pressure she feels as a gang leader when her minions come in and tell her they have a new plan - to feed on Dawn and kill Harmony. As the vampires advance towards Dawn an arrow is fired through one of their hearts. Buffy's here. She kills two more of the minions - the remaining vamp creeps behind her while she speaks with Harmony. Dawn calls out and Buffy engages him in a fight, finally staking him with Harmony's unicorn.

Buffy and Dawn get home just before Joyce and tell her nothing about the night's events. The next day, Dawn writes in her diary at a table in the magic shop - Giles has decided to buy the shop. "She still thinks I'm little miss nobody. Just her dumb little sister. Boy, is she in for a surprise."

@{b}Trivia@{ub}

"I'm not going to Hogwarts": Dawn's anti-magic-shop aside is Buffy paying homage to Harry Potter - it's the school for wizards that Harry attends. The cast and crew, particularly Sarah Michelle Gellar are huge fans of J.K. Rowling's novels.

Spinal Tap: This famous rock-mockumentary features a heavy metal band whose drummers regularly explode and die in mysterious fashions, such as gardening accidents. We last saw a magic shop owner die horribly in @{"Lover's Walk" LINK "LOVERSWALK"}.

