@endnode

@node "OUTOFMYMIND" "Buffy.guide: Out Of My Mind"

@{b}Out Of My Mind@{ub}
5ABB04

"I will know you blood, Slayer. I will make your neck my challice, and drink deep." - Spike

Buffy's out hunting again. She's like an animal, moving on instinct - killing one vamp before he even manages to drag himself out of his grave. Riley appears and takes over the second vamp, slaying him with incredible ease. Another vamp unearths himself and just as Buffy goes to stake him, Spike appears from nowhere and jumps him, then gets himself a bust nose. Buffy jumps in and stakes the vampire, telling Spike she doesn't want him around when she patrolling. Riley agrees, but Spike sees a look Buffy gives him and realises she doen't want Riley there either. As Riley and Buffy walk off, Buffy assures him that @{i}of course @{ui} he wasn't in the way! She also seems impressed with his prowess, and Riley wants to keep patrolling, but Buffy wants to call it a night.

At college, Buffy and Willow discuss a lecture and Willow is impressed with her friend's accademic development. She's been studying a lot - in fact all her time is taken up by studying or training with Giles. Buffy heads to training and invites Willow along. When they arrive Willow admires the shop and then has Tara read her fortune, while Buffy and Giles go to train. When Buffy sees the training space the boys have made up for her she's gobsmacked. Later that night, Harmony calls on Spike, looking for a hide-out under the illusion that she's Buffy's arch-nemesis. Spike attempts to convince Harmony to kill Buffy and offers to be the brains of the duo. Meanwhile, Buffy and Riley have a gratuitous bed-talk scene in orer to improve ratings.

At breakfast, Dawn empties the contents of a cereal box to get to the toy while Joyce makes her an omelette. Joyce suddenly has another headache and looks at Dawn, confused. "Who are you?" she asks, then faints, dropping the breakfast all over the floor. Dawn runs to the phone and dials 911. At the hospital, an intern named Ben assures Buffy that Joyce will be fine while Dawn plays with a stethoscope. She goes round the group, listening to their heartbeats, but when she comes to Riley - his heartbeat seems to be four times as fast as everybody else's!

A doctor has seen to Riley and says his condition is so severe, he should stay in hospital. Of course, she can't force him and his mind is set - he's going home. When the doctor leaves, Buffy tells Riley he should stay, in case he gives himself a heart-attack. Riley is convinced that it's okay though, he was used as a test subject by Initiative scientists for months - his heart just works differently, that's all. Buffy's not convinced and Willow suggests to her somehow contacting the Initiative for help. Suspecting Riley is still being spied on by the government, and his phone may be tapped, Buffy goes to his place and picks up the phone. "Riley's in trouble. He needs help."

Later, Riley is confronted by Grant and two other Initiative agents and told he must come along to be treated. Riley's having none of it, and escapes, beating the hell out of the three of them. Grant finds Buffy and tells her Riley must be treated as soon as possible and that there's a specialist doctor waiting at Sunnydale General Hospital. By late evening, Riley wanders alone while the Scooby Gang hold a meeting. Xander and Anya head to check the docks, and Willow suggests Riley may be hiding at the school. Buffy says the Initiative caves are also a possibility and Giles suggests asking Spike for help. Buffy goes round to Spike's and offers him cash for his help finding Riley.

Over in the doctor's office, the specialist tells Grant that Riley's running out of time. There's a knock at the door and Grant is met with the face of a dead security guard. Harmony cracks the guard's skull against Grant's and knocks him out, then drops the guard on the floor. She walks in followed by Spike, who tosses her a crossbow. Harmony points the weapon at the doctor's head. Spike wants an operation. Spike and Harmony drag the doctor to an operating theatre and attempt to convince him to remove Spike's chip.

The Scooby Gang continue their search for Riley. Willow and Tara check out the school, while Buffy finds a cave, Riley inside repeatedly punching the rock walls. She tells him he's going to die if he doesn't get help, but he tells her to back off. He doesn't want to be a normal person - he doesn't think that's enough for Buffy, who's getting stronger every day. Buffy's upset that he doesn't trust in her, that he thinks she only wants him for his strength. She convinces him to go to the doctor, who right now is operating on Spike, hindered by Harmony's constant babbling.

Buffy and Riley each the hospital and realise what Spike's plan is. Knowing Spike wouldn't have the procedure done at the hospital, Buffy has Grant call round local medical facilities. Meanwhile, the doctor finishes Spike's procedure and stitches him up. Just as Spike contemplates feeding on the doctor, Buffy and Riley show up. Harmony shoots Riley in the leg and the foursome engage in fight. While Harmony beats Riley around like a ragdoll, Spike jumps on Buffy and tries to bite her, but the pain kicks in! Buffy throws him aside and is just getting up when Riley suffers a sudden, enormous pain in his chest, crashes into a table and falls backwards, bringing the table down on himself. Buffy rushes over to Riley while Spike looks for what the doctor "removed" from his head - a penny.

The doctor rushes over to Riley and lifts the table off his unconscious body as Harmony and Spike make a getaway, Spike blowing off steam in the graveyard with a spot of desecration. The doctor operates on Riley and patches him up. Afterwards, Riley and Buffy share a tender moment, both greatly relieved that he's okay. Next day, Grant upsets Riley by telling him there's nothing for him in Sunnydale, and that he belongs with the Initiative. Meanwhile, Buffy calls on Spike, intending to kill him. Spike says fine, end my torment, take me out of this world. Buffy goes as if to stake him but something stops her, and all at once the pair are kissing -- Then Spike wakes up. Looks like the torment is only just beginning for Spike - he has himself a little crush.

@{b}Notes@{ub}

There seems to be a very disproportionate number of male vampires. In the beginning scene of this episode, all three vamps who appear are male. Think back to previous patrolls - the vampires Buffy comes across are almost always male. Is it that vampires are sexist? Who knows? It does seem strange that a show with a female heroine has so few female foes. This makes Harmony all the more annoying - she's just stupid and not even very funny. Bring back Dru!

Although you'll never spot them on camera, all the jars behind the counter at the Magic Box contain ingredients named after the cast and crew. Delights such as Boreanaz Beads, Charisma Charms and Tony's Heads can all be found there.

Spike has become something of a couch potato since he got chipped. Not only does he watch surreal daytime soap Passions in his crypt, it seems from this episode that he follows teen drama 'Dawson's Creek' too. If he can get the WB on his TV though, what does he watch on Tuesdays at 8pm we wonder?

Riley plays basketball to the sound of 'Breathe' by Nickelback. Urrrgh.

