@endnode

@node "BARGAINING1" "Buffy.guide: Bargaining - Part One"

@{b}Bargaining - Part One@{ub}
6ABB01

"Aw, poor Watcher, did your life pass before your eyes? Cup of tea, cup of tea, almost got shagged, cup of tea?" - Spike.

The gang chase an overweight vampire through the graveyard but are having real trouble catching him. Standing from a high vantage point, Willow gives the gang directions telepathically. They drive the vamp over to Buffybot who knocks him down. When she goes to stake him though, he grabs her and knocks her to the floor. Giles and Tara hold the vamp for a second while Spike deals him some punishment. Meanwhile, Willow tips off Xander and Anya about a vamp waiting to jump them. Giles goes to bury an axe in the big vamp but he grabs it and holds Giles up against the railings by his throat with it. Spike jumps on the vamp's back for a second but he throws him off. Then Spike stops to light up a cigarette. Willow can't believe it! Help Giles! But then we see he has - the vamp is on fire, soon his whole body is consumed and he is dust. Spike helps Giles back up and Willow tells them to go help Xander and Anya.

The vamp has Xander in a headlock and Buffybot jumps over to free him. She does, but the vamp has little trouble beating the robot up. Spike comes in to the rescue and gets thrown aside, but he's bought Buffybot enough time to gather herself and she dusts the vamp with ease, before making a rather confusing mess of "pun". Willow's being trying to make Buffybot as much like Buffy was as possible so that their enemies believe Buffy's still around, but there are still some bugs to work out. Next morning, Willow tells Tara her suspicions that there may be a clog-moster under the bed; she can't find her clogs anywhere. Tara suggests it's the Dawn Monster but Dawn, of course, denies all knowledge of any missing clogs.

In the kitchen, Willow tells Buffybot she wants to go over her programming again. Tara thinks Willow has done enough - Buffybot is either ready to face it, or she's not. Xander drops by with tools for Buffybot's much-needed tune-up. The gang can't even let her answer the phone in case Mr. Summers calls and realises something's wrong, and takes Dawn away from them. Xander says they should get to work on fixing Buffybot's fighting skills right away, but Willow says they have bigger problems today: It's Parent-Teacher Day. It goes better than expected however, and she unintentionally sparks up a debate about the lunch program. At the Magic Box, Giles notices the books are a little off, and asks Anya to double-check them. He won't be happy leaving until he knows everything is in order. They end up fighting over an effigy and Xander breaks it up, reminding Anya that she should be nice to Giles if she wants to be in charge when he's in England. Out of Giles' earshot, Anya tells Xander she's sick of waiting to have the shop to herself, and she also wants to tell everyone about their engagement.

Spike's watching over Dawn, and Spike says the teachers probably liked Buffybot because she was predictable. Dawn tells Spike she's okay being left alone but Spike won't go; he blames himself for what happened to Dawn and consequently Buffy's death. Buffybot comes across a vamp in a ridiculous Hanson t-shirt who's about to feed. They fight, Buffybot getting the upper hand until Hanson-boy finds a bottle and smashes it against Buffybot's head. A hole appears and the vamp can see sparks flying inside her. He runs off, leaving her to walk repeatedly into a stack of barrels. At Xander's Anya presents Willow with an Urn of Osiris, and she confirms its authenticity. Willow says it's time, but Xander is suddenly having second thoughts. Willow says no-one is changing their minds: tomorrow night they're bringing Buffy back. No-one knows where Buffy's soul is; she could be in a hell dimension for all they know. Xander's convinced.

Willow gets back home to find the damaged Buffybot and gets to work fixing her up. When Buffybot lapses into her old Spike-loving sexbot self for a second, Spike gets upset and leaves. That night, Dawn can't sleep, and walks through to Buffy's old room, where Buffybot lies on the bed, recharging. She curls up beside this image of her sister and goes to sleep. Giles is testing Buffybot's responses and begins to impart some eastern philosophy as he does so. It's apparently lost on Buffybot, and Giles says her responses are fine, before telling her he wished he could have done more for Buffy. Buffybot asks why he's still here, now his job as Buffy's Watcher is over, and Giles doesn't answer, deep in thought. Meanwhile, the Hanson-loving vamp tells a gang of biker demons that the Slayer has been replaced by a robot. The demons, knowing the Hellmouth is the best place for a party, ride straight over to take the town.

At a beautiful riverside spot, Willow chants a spell which brings forward a fawn. Willow pets the creature for a second, then takes a knife and kills it. She gets to the Magic Box and tells the gang (minus Giles, Dawn and Spike, who've been kept in the dark about their plans) she has the last ingredient for the spell. Anya finds a note from Giles: "I've gone. Not one for goodbyes, I thought it best to slip out quietly. Love to you all, Giles." The gang find Giles at the airport and give him gifts: apple pie and a monster finger puppet. Dawn gives him a card. They call Giles' flight and the gang hug him in turn. He tells them he's just a phone-call away, to be careful, and is gone. Departures... and arrivals; the bikers get into Sunnydale just as the sun sets. Willow, Tara, Anya and Xander perform the ritual by Buffy's grave. Willow's endurance is tested by the spirits and lacerations appear on her arms. Then Tara hears a noise: the biker demons are already at work trashing the town.

Willow's tests continue; she throws up a large snake. Buffybot confronts the biker demons and one of them injures her. She's programmed to find Willow if she's damaged, so goes off to find Willow, the biker demons chasing after her. Buffybot finds Willow and the biker demons are soon all over them, and one runs over the Urn of Osiris - stopping Willow from finishing the spell. Tara and Anya run, and Xander carries Willow, while the bikers attempt to run them over. Xander asks Willow if she's okay, and says he's sorry it didn't work out. It has however, right now Buffy is coming back to life in her coffin... @{"[to be continued...]" LINK "BARGAINING2"}

@{b}Notes@{ub}

The fight scenes at the beginning take on a much more brutal feeling than usual - Buffy is such a spiritually informed and naturally strong fighter that the fights pretty much go her way. When the gang have to fight without her, there's no such choreography - people are on the floor getting repeatedly kicked in the head, and that kind of thing. I suppose it's refreshing in an eyebrow-raising sort of way. Mr. Summers doesn't know his own daughter is dead. Can you imagine? Of course they were estranged - and I hardly speak to either of my parents - but to to not know your own child is dead?!

The obnoxious techno-metal used as the background music for the biker demons is Static-X and, you know what, they suck. I know this one guy who thinks they're the best band in the world. Jesus.

Tara's little monster finger puppet: Her "Grrr.. Arrrg!" is taken from the Mutant Enemy animation shown at the end of each Buffy episode.

