@endnode

@node "DOUBLEMEATPALACE" "Buffy.guide: Double Meat Palace"

@{b}Double Meat Palace@{ub}
6ABB12

"Thit place will kill you." - Spike.

Willow tells Xander and Anya that Buffy's attempt to bust The Trio came up empty - they've cleared out. Buffy comes downstairs to show them her new uniform - she's got a job at Double Meat Palace, a fast food restaurant in town, and today's her first day. "You've seen us in your city or small town across the American West, you've ordered our delicious food from our happy employees, but now you're seeing it in a new way - you're seeing it from behind the counter, because you've just become part of the Double Meat Experience!" Buffy sits watching a training video in the office at Double Meat Palace. Manny, the manager, shuts the tape off when it's finished, and then shows Buffy to the locker-room, where Philip and Timothy, two "lifers - in it for life", are on their break. Philip asks Manny what happened to the "other one", Catherine. Or was it Emily? "Whatever always happens," says Timothy. "She's gone."

Manny takes Buffy to the kitchen, and shows her the production chute. He picks a burger out and offers it to Buffy, telling her what the ingredients are - including a "secret ingredient". Buffy refuses, but he insists, and she asks him through a mouthful of burger what the secret ingredient is. He says it's a "meat process". And so to work - Buffy shadows an experienced employee as he serves a strange old lady, who tells Buffy she might really make it at the palace, unlike some of the kids, who disappear, never to be seen again. On her break, Buffy chews on her free burger like it was cardboard. She takes a look in the freezer and Manny tells her off for going in there, Buffy becoming increasingly freaked-out by the atmosphere at her new job. Xander, Anya, Willow and Dawn pay Buffy a visit and Buffy gets him a Double Meat Meddley. Later, Spike drops by and tells Buffy she shouldn't be working here - she's above this. It will make her unhappy and change her. He tells her to walk with him now, but she won't and needs the money.

Outside, Gary, the boy Buffy was learning from is attacked by someone we don't see, and he doesn't turn up for work the next day. Mndy tells Buffy she'll have to work on the grill to cover for him. Philip shows Buffy how to grill the meat, and asks again what the secret ingredient is - she gets the same answer: it's a meat process. Philip tells Buffy the grease gets everywhere - even deafened him when it built up in his ear. Manny tells Buffy she'll be working a double-shift - but it's ok, she gets extra food! Buffy's pissed, and that's even before she finds out she's on grinding duty. She calls Xander to say she'll be working late. Xander puts the phone down and turns to find a demon in front of him, who says she's be summoned here to wreak vengeance upon him. Anya walks in an has to explain to her friend Halfrek that she's been summoned so Anya can invite her to the wedding, not to kill Xander! Xander, freaked out, leaves. Halfrek asks Anya why she's marrying Xander and Anya says because she loves him, and they're going to be happy together. Halfrek looks unconvinced.

Buffy's on her break and sees Spike outside; she finds him and they have sex against a wall. Amy asks Willow if she can keep her old rat-cage and then asks her how life's working out for her without the help of magic. Willow says she's doing fine, but Amy decides she'll give Willow a little "gift": a spell that makes Willow essentially a vessel for Amy's power. Willow reaches for a vase on the table beside her and it falls apart. When she touches the lamp, it disintegrates. Amy leaves, telling her to enjoy it. Buffy finds a human finger in the mincer and her fears are confirmed. She confronts Manny, accusing him of turning Gary into a burger, but he tries to explain it away by saying that maybe Gary came in early and injured himself. Buffy freaks out and runs into the eating area, where she throws everyone's food on the floor, telling them it's people and they can't eat it. Manny and Philip drag her into the kitchen and she beats them off her. Manny fires her on the spot, and she walks.

Meanwhile, Halfrek stirs the shit with Anya, asking her awkward questions about her relationship with Xander, asking her if she thinks she's making a mistake. Xander and Dawn are playing Fish when Buffy walks in with a burger, and says they have a crisis situation. Buffy shows Dawn the severed finger and says they need to analyse the burger to find out if it contains human flesh. Xander looks round - while Buffy and Dawn were talking, he was tucking into the Double Meat Meddley! Willow arrives, and she's still not back to normal, but she manages to hide it from the gang. Buffy reckons every Double Meat Palace must be doing this - turning their employees into burgers - and says they should bring down the entire corporation. Buffy heads back to the Double Meat Palace to investigate further, while Willow attempts to analyse the remaining meat from Xander's late supper. Buffy finds Manny's foot on the floor in the kitchen. Willow meanwhile, finds that the meat doesn't contain human flesh, but there is something weird about it.

Buffy finds a wig and realises it belongs the strange old she and Gary served together. Wig Lady appears behind Buffy and says she had to wear something to hide this... A large, H.R. Giger-esque snake bursts its way out of the old lady's head and sprays Buffy with a paralyzing fluid. Buffy tries to get away, losing the use of her legs but still able to use her arms. The old lady says she loves the paralysis - it means she can eat her slowly. Willow arrives outside and looks in. She can't see her, and unaware of the danger Buffy is in inside the store, she talks through the drive-thru intercom an tells Buffy that the meat isn't human - in fact there's no meat at all, it's just processed vegetable. She goes on to tell Buffy about her taste of magic from Amy, and says that although it's worn off, she feels like she needs it. It's said that rehabilitation is taken right back to stage one if the addict experiences their drug just once.

Inside, Buffy gets bitten by the snake, as Willow realises something is wrong and ventures inside the store. The Wig Lady turns and sprays her snake-fluid at her. Willow dives out of the way and returns with a cleaver, chopping the snake clean off. The Wig Lady drops to the floor, aparently dead, but the snake continues to squirm near Buffy, and Willow throws it in the mincer. Willow helps Buffy up, and they watch as the snake, oozing green blood, pours out onto the floor below. Next day, Amy calls for Willow, who doesn't want to see Amy after what she did to her. Amy tells her to admit she had a blast, but although Willow doesn't deny it, she knows it was bad for her, and tells Amy that whether or not she's her friend, she'd better stay away. Buffy drops by the Double Meat Palace to return her uniform, and meets the new manager, Lorraine Ross. Buffy tells her she knows about the Double Meat Meddley being vegetable-based, and they make a deal - Buffy gets her job back as long as the secret remains that way.

@{b}Notes@{ub}

I've worked at McDonald's (don't, just don't) and I have to say the training video Buffy watches is a pretty accurate depiction of the training videos new employees get to "enjoy" at the fast food stores. I never got a shag on my break though.

