@endnode

@node "DEADTHINGS" "Buffy.guide: Dead Things"

@{b}Dead Things@{ub}
6ABB13

"Crime tastes funny" - Andrew.

Buffy and Spike share another messy, destructive sex session, and find themselves talking like lovers, even husband and wife, afterwards. Then Spike tells her how amazing she was, he's never been with such an animal. This turns Buffy off and Spike asks what their "thing" means, and Buffy says they don't have a "thing." Spike asks if she really likes him, and Buffy replies, "sometimes." Spike interprets this as meaning that Buffy just likes to have sex with him. He asks her if she trusts him, holding up a pair of cuffs. She says no. At The Trio's new hideout, Jonathan and Andrew fight over pretty much nothing, until Warren calls them over, saying the cerebral dampener is ready to be charged. Jonathan works a spell to charge it up, and Warren says that now they will be able to make any woman their sex slave - and he knows where to start.

Tara pops in to see Buffy at work and she takes a break so they can talk. Buffy tells Tara Willow's doing really well, and then tells her about Spike's ability to harm her, depite his chip being in working order. She feels different, and scared that she'll come back wrong, she asks Tara if she'll find out all she can about the spell Willow use to bring her back. Tara thinks Buffy's fine, but she'll check just to put her friend's mind at rest. Warren finds @{"Katrina" LINK "ABOUTKATRINA"} at a bar, and she makes it clear she's uninterested in him. Until, that is, Warren gets out the small, shiny globe he calls a "cerebral dampner" and Katrina tells him she loves him. Buffy gets home and Xander's teaching Dawn how to dance for the wedding. Xander suggests they go out for a beer, but Buffy says she should stay and spend time with Dawn - who informs her that she's sleeping over at Janice's again. Buffy's amazed that Dawn's trying to pull that one again, but this time she's not lying. Buffy says that since she's here now, and they can finally spend time togther, can't she stay over at Janice's another night? Dawn says Janice's mum is cooking mexican, and it's not as if she knew Buffy would be home. Buffy decides she'll have that beer after all.

The Trio pay a toast to crime, and admire their new slave. Warren says he's going first, and he takes her through to the bedroom, where she pushes him up against the wall, and kisses him. He tells her to get on her knees, but before anything happens, the effect of Waren's gadget wears off and she realises who she is again. She pushes him out of the room and asks him what the hell he did to her, and Warren shouts to Andrew and Jonathan to get the dampener. Andrew tries to use the dampener on her, but it doesn't work. She asks Warren what his problem is, an tells them all their sick - this is rape. Katrina tries to escape, and Jonathan and Andrew try in vain to hold her back. Warren follows her up the stairs to the door, and tries to pull her down, she pushes him away, but he follows and grabs her again. This time she scratches his face, but he still doesn't give up, and she drops to the floor. She makes another grabs for the door as Warren grabs the wine bottle and brings it down on her head. Katrina stops moving.

Jonathan and Andrew seem to know straight-away that something is wrong, unlike Warren who simply tells them to charge the dampener again and it'll all be okay. Jonathan and Andrew are reluctant, since Katrina's words have made them realize how wrong this is. Andrew goes to check Katrina and confirms his worst fear - she's dead. Warren checks her himself, and asks Jonathan if he knows a spell to revive her or at least teleport the body out of here. He doesn't, and Andrew says the only demons he could summon to eat the body would go for them too. Warren hatches a plan to take care of the body and Buffy at the same time. At the Bronze, Buffy sits out on the dancing and goes upstairs. As she watches her friends dance, Spike approaches her and observes that no matter how much she tries to be with her friends, she ends up hiding in the dark, with him. He wondersb alound what they would think of her if they knew, and lifts her skirt. As they have sex, Spike tells her not to close her eyes, but to watch her friends. "Tell me you don't love getting away with this right under their noses."

Next morning, Xander and Anya are heading for the Magic Box when they meet Tara. Xander excuses himself, and Willow tells Tara she's doing much better, and has managed 32 days without magic. Tara tells Willow she's looking for Buffy, and asks that she tells Buffy she needs to see her, and it's important. Before Tara leaves, she tells Willow she's glad she's doing better. Later that night at the cemetary, Buffy approaches Spike's place and stands outside the door. Spike senses her there and they both stand either side of the door, palms upon the wood, as if they were touching directly. But when Spike opens the door, Buffy is gone. Trying to put her mind off Spike, Buffy gets on with her patrol, and hears a scream in the woods. She runs to the source of the scream, and sees a demon in a cloak chasing a girl. She dives for the demon but he disappears. Buffy gets up and her surroundings are deserted. Then she hears a noise, like the time shifting she's experienced before, and Katrina is apparently crying on the ground. She goes over to help, and time shifts again, and she's alone.

Buffy puts her hands up over her ears in distress. Time shifts again, and she sees Spike on the floor with a bloodied nose, asking why she hit him. Time shifts yet again and Katrina is on the floor while Spike and Buffy battle four cloaked demons. Time keeps switching - sometimes there's just her and Spike there, sometimes the demons are there too along with Katrina. Buffy's alone - Buffy's snapping a demon's back - Buffy's alone again. Then Spike shouts as another demon comes for Buffy and she punches it out of the way. Katrina runs for Buffy's help and grabs her, and in a reflex, Buffy punches her in the head. Katrina falls down an embankment and Buffy follows, leaving Spike to kill the demons. He punches his hand straight through the last one and joins Buffy, who's found Katrina dead. From the bushes another "Katrina" watches as Spike tells Buffy they have to split. Spike says he'll take her home to bed, and he'll come back and dispose of the body. "Katrina" comes back into the van and morphs back into her original form - it's Jonathan.

Buffy can't sleep properly, and when she does, dreams about sex with Spike all mixed up with Katrina's "death". She wakes and goes into Dawn's room. Buffy tells Dawn she loves her, and Dawn can tell something is wrong. Buffy tells her there was an accident, a girl got hurt, and she died. Buffy says she has to turn herself in to the police - it's her duty. Dawn accuses her of using this as some kind of excuse to get away from her and this life. Buffy goes to the station, and before she goes in, Spike stops her. Buffy asks him what he did with the body, but he won't go into detail, saying they'll never find it. Just then, two policemen jump into a patrol car saying a body has been found in the river. Spike asks why she wants to throw her life away - think of all the people she's saved. They get into a physical fight and Buffy pins him down and beats him senseless around the head, telling him he's a soul-less and could not ever understand why it hurts so bad for her to have killed someone. She realises what a mess she's made of him and shows some remorse, but goes into the police station. The guy at the desk is busy on the phone, and he gets the ID of the dead girl - Katrina. Buffy remembers Katrina from her first encounter with Warren, and realises she might not be to blame afterall. She leaves before the policeman gets off the phone.

Anya, in full-on Giles mode, identifies the demons Buffy was attacked by - Rusindi - and explains that these demons' presense creates a temporal disturbance. Buffy still thinks it was Warren however, and not the demons themselves, who killed Katrina. She says they must find The Trio - they shouldn't get away with this. The Trio themselves are checking the Coroner's report, Katrin's death has been ruled a suicide. Tara assures Buffy that she's fine - moving her between dimensions or from wherever she was, has altered her on a molecular level - enough to confuse Spike's chip - but she's still Buffy. Buffy says she must have missed something - how else could she be acting like this, letting Spike do what he does to her? Tara realises Buffy means she's been sleeping with Spike and Buffy begs her not to tell anyone. Tara promises, and asks Buffy if she loves Spike. It's okay if she does, and it's okay if she doesn't - she's been going through a rough time. Buffy says it's not okay to use someone and she doesn't want forgiveness, and she cries, knealing in front of Tara.

@{b}Notes@{ub}

Buffy's line "So that's why time went all David Lynch?" is of course a reference to the fantastic filmmaker David Lynch, and more importantly, the insanity and weirdness that shapes his art. My favorite Lynch film, 'Eraserhead', is one of those films that everyone either loves or hates - the whole thing is so bizarre it defies any adjective you might throw at it, and is so far away from Hollywood, it could be on Uranus. That's a good thing.

@{b}Goto:@{ub}   @{" String Search " SYSTEM "newcli WINDOW=CON:20/20/400//Buffy from Buffy.guide.cli"}@{"?" LINK "SEARCHREADME"}  @{" Major Events " LINK "EVENTS"}  @{" Characters " LINK "CHARACTERPROFILES"}  @{" Vocabulary " LINK "VAMPVOC"}  @{" Main Page " LINK "MAIN"}

@endnode

@node "OLDERANDFARAWAY" "Buffy.guide: Older And Far Away"

@{b}Older And Far Away@{ub}
6ABB14

"Mm, I think he seemed pretty cute, yeah!" - Clem.

The night before Buffy's birthday, Buffy goes out to patrol, leaving Dawn home alone. At the graveyard, Buffy comes across a large warrior demon with a sword. An aparent master of disguise, he disappears for a few heart-stopping seconds after disarming Buffy. He re-appears and Buffy manages to take his sword from him. She sticks it in his gut and a wave of energy knocks Buffy over as he falls to his knees. Beforre Buffy gets up, we see the demon shift into a liquid-like form and embedd himself in the blade of his sword. Once this is completed, there's a rough image of the demon - like a ghostly reflection - in the shiny blade. Buffy gets up to find the demon has apparenty scarpered, and decides she'll keep the sword for herself.

At the Magic Box, Anya wonders if they should have candles at Buffy's party. Xander tells Willow that Buffy wants Tara there, and Willow says that's fine by her. Dawn comes in and asks the gang if they want to take her to the mall for Buffy's presents, but they're all busy and Dawn has to go alone. Dawnn gets home later and empties her pockets of several items of jewelery, all with price tags on. Under her coat, she's wearing a black leather jacket, and she models it for herself in front of the mirror. The security tag is still in the sleeve. Next day in school, Dawn is called to the guidance office. There's a new cousellor, who we recognise as the human manifestation of Anya's friend, Halfrek. Dawn tells her that people don't hang out with her much, and she wishes they would stay with her.

It's party-time and Xander and Anya gently let slip that they have a male friend coming over who they home she'll find a lot in common with. Tara arrives and asks Buffy how she is. Buffy says she's okay, and Spike won't be making an appearance tonight. Willow comes downstairs and Buffy pretends to have something urgent to do, and Willow and Tara share an awkward but touching greeting. Tara goes for something to drink in the kitchen with Buffy, and Spike comes in the back door with @{"Clem" LINK "ABOUTCLEM"}, citing the old "the more the merrier" theory. Then Xander walks in with Richard, the friend he and Anya invited. Xander tells Buffy Richard needs somewhere to park his car and tells him Buffy will show him where.

Dawn asks Anya if it's time for presents yet, and she says that Buffy's busy right now "making a grown-up friend." Dawn explains that she does understand how these things work, and Anya simply pats her on the head, condescendingly. Spike gets Buffy aside and asks her if she wants to slip away from the party with him for a while. Buffy playfully accuses him of being jealous of Richard, which Spike of course vehemently denies. For a present, Willow has got Buffy a battery-operated massager, and Dawn presents her with the leather jacket. Buffy notices the still-attached security tag, and Dawn says "that's weird". Xander and Anya wheel in a beautiful weapons chest for Buffy that Xander made himself. Buffy's speechless, and Dawn's a little bitter that Buffy wasn't so enthusiastic about her present.

Buffy's friend from work, Sophie, arrives and Buffy introduces everyone while Dawn gets the door. She looks out, apparently sensing someone out there, but we don't see anyone until Dawn closes the door. Then Halfrek steps out of hiding and declares Dawn's wish granted. Inside, Richard asks Buffy if she'd like a drink and she says she's okay right now. When he's gone, Spike talks to Buffy, and takes her hand, then places it on his pants. Tara sees and Buffy walks off, leaving Tara to smile questioningly at Spike. His excuse is a muscle cramp. Xander and Anya argue in an annoyingly cute way about who's going to go and get more beer, and Willow says she'll go. Sophie says she'll come along and help, even though she's allergic to beer (among many other things). Neither of them feel like moving when it comes to it, however, and Willow rests her head on the table, tired.

A little later, Buffy, Richard, Anya and Dawn play monopoly while Xander, Spike, Clem and Tara play Poker. The party looks like going on all night, and it does. In the morning, everyone sits watching cartoons, those that aren't asleep that is. Richard needs to get to work in a few minutes but doens't know why he's not leaving. Spike freaks Richard out by joking about eating him and Buffy tries to kick him out, but neither of them can get the door. Willow and Tara meet in the kitchen and talk about the strange feeling they're experiencing - wanting to leave the house, but not wanting to. In the living room, everyone agrees they have other things they should be doing, but none of the will leave. Something is keeping them there. Dawn gets upset that everyone wants to leave ("Being stuck in here with me would really suck, right?"). She storms upstairs and the gang follow.

They ask if she knows anything or did anything, but she denies all knowledge, and screams at them to leave. Buffy suggests Tara uses magic to get some idea of what's happening, but Tara didn't bring any supplies. Willow admits she has kept a few things, in case of emergency. Tara works her mojo, while Richard gets increasingly freaked out by the day's events. Unfortunately, Tara's release spell releases the demon from his sword, which Buffy brought home with her. The gang still can't get out. The demon lunges at the gang, cutting Richard deep in the gut, before disappearing. The gang are still trapped by nightfall, and they begin to hear noises coming from the walls of the house. Tara and Willow watch over Richard, Buffy stalks the demon, and Anya freaks out about feeling trapped.

The demon materialises behind Xander and attacks him, and Spike comes to the rescue but gets thrown down the hallway. Buffy runs through and she fight the demon, trying to take his sword. Xander gets his arm slashed, and despite their best efforts, Spike and Buffy fail to take the demon's sword, and he shrinks away again. Buffy finds Dawn and asks her how she is and Dawn tells her how alone she feels - Buffy has all her friends, but she has no-one. Anya, meanwhile, tells Willow she should forget her magic rule just this once, to get them out. But Willow refuses on principal, and Anya starts to bitch at her, when Tara tells her to back off. Anya says she'll do it herself. Upstairs Buffy hears from Dawn about the new guidance counsellor at school and asks her if she happened to make a wish to her? Dawn says she kinda did.

Anya's going insane, and believing Dawn knows something, she starts to search through her room. She finds Dawn's jewellery box with the Magic Box items inside. She asks Dawn how she could do this after how much she's helped her, and Buffy realises the present from Dawn - the jacket - has been stolen, and that's why the tag's still on. Buffy tells Anya that Dawn made a wish to a guideance counsellor, and she realises it's Halfrek. She calls Halfrek and she appears, only to be slain by the sword demon. Buffy and Spike manage to take the demon's sword, and Buffy stabs the demon once more, just before he disappears again. He retreats back into his sword, and then Buffy breaks the sword in two. Anya goes for Halfrek's pendant - her powercentre - but she gets up and is apparently fine.

Halfrek and Spike recognise each other but don't explain to the rest of the gang why. Halfrek explains that her niche in the vengeance market is bad parents. She tells the gang they deserve to be cursed for ignorance of Dawn's pain. Halfrek tells them they now have all the time in the world togther, then tries to leave - but she can't. She has to lift her own curse before she can leave, and so she does. The gang breathe a collective sigh of relief. Tara takes Willow's remaining magic stuff away and Willow says she kept it as a "safety-net" in case things got bad. Tara says she unerstands, but now it's time to work without it. Things did get really bad, and she still refused to used magic - ther's a hint of pride in Tara's voice and she smiles. Spike opens the front door, and Xander and Anya take Richard to hospital. Everyone leaves, Clem thanking Buffy for a great party, leaving Buffy and Dawn in the house to spend some quality time at last.

@{b}Notes@{ub}

"Man, when a nerd goes into hiding, he really goes into hiding." It's funny how much nerd-bashing there is on the show when despite its popularity, it's exactly the kind of show that "nerds" hold dear to their hearts.

Tara taunting Spike about the "muscle cramp" in his pants is fantastic. We haven't seen nearly enough humour from Tara. Also, her line "if you try, you're going to have to go through me first" may be a reference back to @{"Family" LINK "FAMILY"}, in which Buffy and the gang told Tara's family that they'd have to go through them first if they want to take Tara away against her will.

