@node "ABOUTAMPATA" "Buffy.guide: About Ampata"

@{b}Ampata@{ub}
(Ara Celi)

Appeared in @{"Inca Mummy Girl" LINK "INCAMUMMYGIRL"} (1997).

Released when the seal that held her at bay was broken, this 500-year-old Incan mummy wreaks havoc on Sunnydale. Ampatta can only continue to live if she periodically drains the life out of an unwitting victim with a deadly kiss.

@{b}Goto:@{ub}   @{" String Search " SYSTEM "newcli WINDOW=CON:20/20/400//Buffy from Buffy.guide.cli"}@{"?" LINK "SEARCHREADME"}  @{" Major Events " LINK "EVENTS"}  @{" Characters " LINK "CHARACTERPROFILES"}  @{" Vocabulary " LINK "VAMPVOC"}  @{" Main Page " LINK "MAIN"}
@endnode

@node "ABOUTAMY" "Buffy.guide: About Amy Madison"

@{b}Amy Madison@{ub}
(Elizabth Anne Allen)

1996 - present, in sporadic appeareances.

Amy was the show's first introduction to magic. Her own mother was a witch, and used a body-swapping spell on Amy in order to relive her old cheerleading days (see @{"The Witch" LINK "THEWITCH"}). When Buffy intervened, Amy's mum got pissed and tried to curse Buffy. Buffy deflected the spell back at the witch, who found herself stuck forever inside a cheerleading trophy at Sunnydale High. Despite her bad experiences, Amy inherited her mother's enthisiasm for magic, and in @{"Bewitched, Bothered and Bewildered" LINK "BEWITCHED"} she helped @{"Xander" LINK "ABOUTXANDER"} cast a love spell on Cordelia, which backfired and made the whole of Sunnydale's female population fall for Xander's charms.

In @{"Gingerbread" LINK "GINGERBREAD"}, following the apparent black-magic murder of two young children, Amy along with Buffy and Willow were about to be burnt at the stake and Amy decided her best course of action was to turn herself into a rat and escape. Willow kept the Amy-rat for three years, only changing her back, unknowingly, for a few seconds in @{"Something Blue" LINK "SOMETHINGBLUE"}. Willow worked out the right spell to reverse Amy's condition in @{"Smashed" LINK "SMASHED"}, and Amy proved to be a bad influence on Willow, whose addiction to magic had already driven @{"Tara" LINK "ABOUTTARA"} away from her. After Amy introduced Willow to a powerful warlock called @{"Wreck" LINK "ABOUTRACK"}, Willow spun out of control, even putting Dawn in danger (see @{"Wrecked" LINK "WRECKED"}). Willow subsequently gave up magic, cutting herself off from Amy.

@{b}Goto:@{ub}   @{" String Search " SYSTEM "newcli WINDOW=CON:20/20/400//Buffy from Buffy.guide.cli"}@{"?" LINK "SEARCHREADME"}  @{" Major Events " LINK "EVENTS"}  @{" Characters " LINK "CHARACTERPROFILES"}  @{" Vocabulary " LINK "VAMPVOC"}  @{" Main Page " LINK "MAIN"}
@endnode

@node "ABOUTANDREW" "Buffy.guide: About Andrew"

@{b}Andrew Wells@{ub}
(Tom Lenk)

###todo

Second in command of @{"The Trio" LINK "ABOUTTRIO"}, and in many ways the most pathetic of the three (he posseses neither @{"Warren" LINK "ABOUTWARREN"}'s intellect or @{"Jonathan" LINK "ABOUTJONATHAN"}'s conscience). Legend has it that Andrew summoned forth demon monkeys to attack a high school play ("Everyone was like, 'Run, Juliet!!'"), but, typically, finds most people better remember his brother, Tucker, for his hell-hound attack in @{"The Prom" LINK "THEPROM"}.

After @{"Willow" LINK "ABOUTWILLOW"} kills Warren for shooting @{"Tara" LINK "ABOUTTARA"}, she comes for Jonathan and Andrew, who escape in the general direction of Mexico.

@{b}Goto:@{ub}   @{" String Search " SYSTEM "newcli WINDOW=CON:20/20/400//Buffy from Buffy.guide.cli"}@{"?" LINK "SEARCHREADME"}  @{" Major Events " LINK "EVENTS"}  @{" Characters " LINK "CHARACTERPROFILES"}  @{" Vocabulary " LINK "VAMPVOC"}  @{" Main Page " LINK "MAIN"}
@endnode

@node "ABOUTANGEL" "Buffy.guide: About Angel"

@{b}Angel@{ub}
(David Boreanaz)

1996 - 2000 (as a regular character)

Angel was born early in the eighteenth century. By 1753 he was living in Galway, as a drunkard and womaniser. There he was made a vampire by Darla, and, as "Angelus", subsequently travelled Europe, leaving a trail of destruction in his wake, more than earning The Master's description of him as "The most vicious creature I ever met."

When Angel first encountered @{"Buffy" LINK "ABOUTBUFFY"}, it was as a shadowy advisor who warned her about The Master's plan to escape. It wasn't until @{"Angel" LINK "ANGEL"} that he revealed his true form to Buffy. Tending to his wounds after a skirmish with three vampires, Angel tells Buffy he's an orphan, and that vampires killed his parents "a long while ago". He warns that they should not become involved, but they kiss, and Angel morphs into vampire form, and flees. Later Buffy confronts him, her feelings in turmoil, and Angel admits that he killed his family: "for a hundred years I offered an ugly death to everyone I met". Giles cautions Buffy against falling in love with Angel, to no avail, although he does admit that the Slayer falling in love with a vampire is "poetic".

Angel's reign of terror ended when he killed a young gypsy girl offered to him by Darla. The girl's family cursed him by restoring his soul, making it impossible for him to kill again. In @{"Surprise" LINK "SURPRISE"} it is revealed that Jenny Calendar was sent to Sunnydale by the gypsy tribe to make sure that Angel never experiences one moment of happiness: if he does, his soul will vanish again, and his evil nature will take control again. Despite Jenny's attentions, Angel and Buffy spend a fateful night together. Angel awakens in pain: he has crossed to the dark side again, and teams up with Spike and Drusilla, crushing Buffy's love in the process.

Angelus goes on to attempt the awakening of the demon Acathla, creating a portal to hell. Buffy goes to fight him while Willow attempts to restore him soul, using a spell based on @{"Jenny" LINK "ABOUTJENNY"}'s work. Tragically, Willow's curse works after Angelus has opened the vortex, and Buffy has to kill her own lover to seal the portal (see Becoming parts @{"one" LINK "BECOMING1"} and @{"two" LINK "BECOMING2"}.) He returns from hell at the end of @{"Faith, Hope and Trick" LINK "FAITHHOPETRICK"} and Buffy cares for him, hiding him from her friends until Xander finds them together in @{"Revelations" LINK "REVELATIONS"}. Angel proves his worth to the Scooby Gang again, but he leaves for LA after their battle with the Mayor in @{"Graduation Day - Part Two" LINK "GDAY2"}, knowing he can't offer Buffy the future she deserves. In LA, he finds his vocation as a private detective and you can watch his adventures on the aptly-titled 'Angel' series.

@{b}Goto:@{ub}   @{" String Search " SYSTEM "newcli WINDOW=CON:20/20/400//Buffy from Buffy.guide.cli"}@{"?" LINK "SEARCHREADME"}  @{" Major Events " LINK "EVENTS"}  @{" Characters " LINK "CHARACTERPROFILES"}  @{" Vocabulary " LINK "VAMPVOC"}  @{" Main Page " LINK "MAIN"}
@endnode

@node "ABOUTANYA" "Buffy.guide: About Anya"

@{b}Anya@{ub}
(Emma Caulfield)

1999 - present

###todo - fear of bunnies

After being wronged by her lover, Anya became Anyanka, "the patron saint of scorned women" - a vegeance demon who granted the wishes of women who'd been neglected or cheated on. After Xander cheats on @{"Cordelia" LINK "ABOUTCOR"} with @{"Willow" LINK "ABOUTWILLOW"}, Cordelia wishes to Anyanka that Buffy (who she blames for the entire relationship) had never moved to Sunnydale in @{"The Wish" LINK "THEWISH"} but soon realises her mistake and seeks out Giles, who destroys Anyanka's power-centre. Anya is rendered human once more and everything is back to normal.

Settling back into life as a human, Anya looks for a date for @{"The Prom" LINK "THEPROM"}. Against the odds, Xander and Anya bond and become a serious couple. Xander proposes to her but on the day of their wedding, Xander is visited by a demon claiming to be him as an old man, who shows him a grim image of his future with Anya. Freaked, Xander walks and soon realises his mistake, but it's over. Anya becomes Anyanka once again and seeks out vengeance on Xander.

Playing Xander's love interest on "Buffy" is not a stretch for the enchanting Emma. She has been the object of affection on many television shows, ranging from sitcoms ("Weird Science"), to dramas ("Silk Stalkings"), to soap operas ("General Hospital"). After growing up in sunny San Diego, Emma moved into theater as a teenager. Her experience landed her guest starring roles on television shows. She has acted opposite heartthrobs Don Johnson on "Nash Bridges" and Lorenzo Lamas on "Renegade". Her favorite role, however, was as Nurse Penny Brady on "Saved By The Bell: The College Years". She enjoyed acting in front of the live studio audience because it reminded her most of stage performance.

Emma's breakthrough was her recurring character in the 1995-96 season of Beverly Hills 90210 as Brandon's love interest, Susan Keats. This exposure landed her the role of Anyanka. While Emma loves working on "Buffy", she has a cynical attitude towards her career. "I don't know that I want to act 15 years from now. I mean, I love the process of acting, but not the masochism." Having already earned a degree in Psychology, she won't have to worry about making a living fifteen years from now no matter what her occupation.

@{b}Goto:@{ub}   @{" String Search " SYSTEM "newcli WINDOW=CON:20/20/400//Buffy from Buffy.guide.cli"}@{"?" LINK "SEARCHREADME"}  @{" Major Events " LINK "EVENTS"}  @{" Characters " LINK "CHARACTERPROFILES"}  @{" Vocabulary " LINK "VAMPVOC"}  @{" Main Page " LINK "MAIN"}
@endnode

@node "ABOUTAPRIL" "Buffy.guide: About April"

@{b}April@{ub}
(Shonda Farr)

Appears in @{"I Was Made To Love You" LINK "IWASMADETOLOVEYOU"}.

Created by @{"Warren" LINK "ABOUTWARREN"} as the perfect girlfriend, ###todo

