@node "ABOUTCOR" "Buffy.guide: About Cordelia Chase"

@{b}Cordelia Chase@{ub}
(Charisma Carpenter)

1996 - 2000

Completely self-centred, Cordelia Chase aspired to be the most popular girl in school. She surrounded herself with her own cliquey friends, and looked down haughtily on lesser mortals, including @{"Buffy" LINK "ABOUTBUFFY"}, @{"Willow" LINK "ABOUTWILLOW"} and, especially, @{"Xander" LINK "ABOUTXANDER"}. Tactless and outspoken, Cordelia was devoid of compassion for others, and obsessed with her appearance. Primarily concerned for her own safety, Cordelia often found herself on the periphery of Buffy's adventures, (for example, she was competing to become a cheerleader when Amy began using magic to bump off her rivals, and was temporarily blinded).

Cordelia has had trouble finding boyfriends who meet her exacting standards, but there seems to be no shortage of potential candidates. Her only real rival in Sunnydale was Buffy who, to her amazement, some people, most notably Angel, preferred. Her close encounter with Marcie Ross in @{"Invisible Girl" LINK "INVISIBLEGIRL"} changed Cordelia's frosty attitude, and she soon became much closer to Buffy and the gang. In the middle of a rather harrowing adventure @{"What's My Line? - Part 2" LINK "WHATSMYLINE2"} she was trapped in a basement with Xander, and, driven by fate into each other's arms, she finally had to admit her love for him. However, it's not something she was entirely comfortable with, and was very anxious that as few people as possible found out that she was dating a geek.

When Xander cheats on her, Cordy stops returning his calls. Blaming Buffy for making Xander cool enough to go out with, Cordy makes a wish that Buffy had never come to Sunnydale (see @{"The Wish" LINK "THEWISH"}.) After @{"Graduation Day" LINK "GDAY1"}, Cordy moved to LA in the hope of pursuing an acting career, where she came across @{"Angel" LINK "ABOUTANGEL"} and together with his friend Doyle, they become an evil-fighting trio operating under the name of 'Angel Investigations'.

Charisma Carpenter was born in Las Vegas, and was named after a brand of perfume! She entered show business after graduating from high school, appearing in dozens of TV commercials before landing a guest role in "Baywatch". She played Ashley Green in Aaron Spelling's short-lived NBC series "Malibu Shores" and was pondering her next move when she was asked to join the cast of "Buffy The Vampire Slayer".

@{b}Goto:@{ub}   @{" String Search " SYSTEM "newcli WINDOW=CON:20/20/400//Buffy from Buffy.guide.cli"}@{"?" LINK "SEARCHREADME"}  @{" Major Events " LINK "EVENTS"}  @{" Characters " LINK "CHARACTERPROFILES"}  @{" Vocabulary " LINK "VAMPVOC"}  @{" Main Page " LINK "MAIN"}
@endnode

