@node "ABOUTDAWN" "Buffy.guide: About Dawn"

@{b}Dawn Summers@{ub}
(Michelle Trachtenberg)

2001 - present

When Glory came close to finding the key which would open a portal to demon dimensions, the monks who protected it found a way to hide it in human form. They sent it to Buffy in the form of a younger sister, Dawn, and created memories for everyone in contact with Dawn, knowing that Buffy would guard Dawn with her life. Forever shielded from the demons and evils Buffy has to fight every week, Dawn felt left out and alone for a long while, and predictably went a little crazy when she found out she was a key - a simple object - in @{"Blood Ties" LINK "BLOODTIES"}. Dawn's been through a lot for someone so young, even by Buffy standards. Despite this, in @{"Grave" LINK "GRAVE"} Dawn finally proved to her sister that she didn't need shielding from the world, and turns out to be a gifted fighter - perhaps there's Slayer blood in her.

###todo

Michelle Trachtenberg previously worked with Sarah Michelle Gellar on the American daytime soap All My Children. She also starred in the children's film Harriet the Spy, written by Buffy scribe Doug Petrie.

