@node "ABOUTGLORY" "Buffy.guide: About Glory"

@{b}Glory@{ub}
(Clare Kramer)

Glory was an age-old God, physically the strongest foe Buffy has faced. On their first encounter, Glory threw Buffy around so hard she left dents in the walls. Glory shares a body with the unwilling Ben, an intern at Sunnydale General Hospital who befriends Buffy and the gang. Referred to by the monks who created Dawn as "the Beast", she's also been addressed as "that which cannot be named"; such is her age, she pre-dates language.###todo


###todo

Glorious Debut: Sunnydale's public enemy number one makes her debut, in the stunning form of Clare Kramer. Having worked with Eliza Dushku on hit cheerleading comedy Bring it On, Clare has obviously learned how to act as mad as a brush. Kramer keeps a journal on every role she plays to maintain continuity and character development throughout each project she works on. Plus, she looks great in a red dress.


Clare Kramer, who played Glory throughout season five of Buffy, revealed that she was delighted to be giving Buffy hell once more.
Referring to her cameo in season premiere Lessons, Kramer told the Knox News website: "I think [Glory] has evolved a little bit. She's been through it a little bit. "We'll just to have to see what (circumstance) has done to her."
Although future plot lines are very much under wraps, our spies indicate that Clare will appear in more episodes throughout the season.
Despite Glory being a bad girl, Kramer defends her as being "a strong-willed woman," and explained how she approached the part.
"When I came into my audition for the part," she says, "I was thinking of Jack Nicholson in The Shining, and that is how I have always played her."


@{b}Goto:@{ub}   @{" String Search " SYSTEM "newcli WINDOW=CON:20/20/400//Buffy from Buffy.guide.cli"}@{"?" LINK "SEARCHREADME"}  @{" Major Events " LINK "EVENTS"}  @{" Characters " LINK "CHARACTERPROFILES"}  @{" Vocabulary " LINK "VAMPVOC"}  @{" Main Page " LINK "MAIN"}
@endnode

@node "ABOUTGWENDOLYN" "Buffy.guide: About Gwendolyn"

@{b}Gwendolyn Post@{ub}
()

Appears in @{"Revelations" LINK "REVELATIONS"}.

Ms. Post was a Watcher kicked out by The Council for misuse of dark power. She befriended Buffy and the gang by posing as Faith's new Watcher, but she was really after the Glove of Myhnegon, which grants its wearer evil powers of destruction.

@{b}Goto:@{ub}   @{" String Search " SYSTEM "newcli WINDOW=CON:20/20/400//Buffy from Buffy.guide.cli"}@{"?" LINK "SEARCHREADME"}  @{" Major Events " LINK "EVENTS"}  @{" Characters " LINK "CHARACTERPROFILES"}  @{" Vocabulary " LINK "VAMPVOC"}  @{" Main Page " LINK "MAIN"}
@endnode

@node "ABOUTHANSANDGRETA" "Buffy.guide: About Hans and Greta"

@{b}Hans and Greta@{ub}
(,)

Appear in @{"Gingerbread" LINK "GINGERBREAD"}.

Beginning their evil excursions in 1649, Hans and Greta resurface every 50 years to wreak havoc on small towns by brainwashing the townspeople into killing the innocent in a witchhunt. By staging their own ritualistic deaths in Sunnydale, Hans and Greta coaxed the parents of Sunnydale into burning Buffy, Willow and Amy at the stake, but quick thinking on Buffy's part revealed Hans and Greta's true demonic form.

@{b}Goto:@{ub}   @{" String Search " SYSTEM "newcli WINDOW=CON:20/20/400//Buffy from Buffy.guide.cli"}@{"?" LINK "SEARCHREADME"}  @{" Major Events " LINK "EVENTS"}  @{" Characters " LINK "CHARACTERPROFILES"}  @{" Vocabulary " LINK "VAMPVOC"}  @{" Main Page " LINK "MAIN"}
@endnode

@node "ABOUTHARMONY" "Buffy.guide: About Harmony"

@{b}Harmony Kendall@{ub}
(Mercedes McNab)

1996 - ###todo

Harmony was one of Cordelia's superficial friends from Sunnydale High who fought valiantly in the Graduation Day Battle. However, no one saw her get bitten and turn into a vampire during the melee. Wishing to kill the people she merely teased in high school, she entered an abusive relationship with Spike who promised to help her dispose of her ex-classmates. She helped Spike find the elusive Gem of Amara, granting him the power to expose himself to sunlight. Appears in @{"Harsh Light of Day" LINK "HARSHLIGHT"} and gets herself a ridiculous vampire gang together in season five.

