@node "ABOUTJOYCE" "Buffy.guide: About Joyce"

@{b}Joyce@{ub}
(Kristine Sutherland)

1996 - 2001

(###todo - add buffy's dad here, and in seperate node)

Joyce, as Buffy's mum, must have had the patience of a saint. Despite multiple inexplicable trashings, she managed to keep the house in great shape despite being a single mother. She learnt Buffy was the Slayer during @{"Becoming - Part Two" LINK "BECOMING2"} and understandably freaked, which along with Buffy's guilt at killing Angel to save the world led to the absence of Joyce's only daughter for an entire summer.

Since then, Joyce has tried her best to support Buffy in her work and, among other things, has had sex with @{"Giles" LINK "ABOUTGILES"} while under the influence of mind-controlling chocolate during @{"Band Candy" LINK "BANDCANDY"} and unknowingly invited Dracula himself into her house for a cup of coffee (see @{"Buffy Vs. Dracula" LINK "BUFFYVSDRACULA"}.)

After collapsing in @{"Out Of My Mind" LINK "OUTOFMYMIND"} and subsequently experiencing severe headaches, Joyce goes to hospital for a cat-scan, and in @{"Shadow" LINK "SHADOW"} finds out she has a brain tumour. The tumour is operated on and removed apparently successfully, but sadly just a few weeks later, Buffy finds her mother dead at home (see @{"The Body" LINK "THEBODY"}.)

@{b}Goto:@{ub}   @{" String Search " SYSTEM "newcli WINDOW=CON:20/20/400//Buffy from Buffy.guide.cli"}@{"?" LINK "SEARCHREADME"}  @{" Major Events " LINK "EVENTS"}  @{" Characters " LINK "CHARACTERPROFILES"}  @{" Vocabulary " LINK "VAMPVOC"}  @{" Main Page " LINK "MAIN"}
@endnode

@node "ABOUTTHEJUDGE" "Buffy.guide: About The Judge"

@{b}The Judge@{ub}
()

Appears in @{"Surprise" LINK "SURPRISE"}.

An ancient and indestructable demon warrior, the judge once roamed the earth, laying waste to human civilization in the name of all that's evil. Since it was not possible to kill him with normal weapons, the only way to defeat him was to chop him up and separate the pieces from eachother. As a birthday gift to Drusilla, Spike orchestrated the Judge's resurrection, bringing the pieces back together. Once his parts were joined, the Judge was reanimated.

