@node "ABOUTOZ" "Buffy.guide: About Oz"

@{b}Oz@{ub}
(Seth Green)

1997 - 2000

Oz was a senior student at Sunnydale who plays guitar in a band called Dingoes Ate My Baby (a reference to the story of Lindy Chamberlain which was dramatised in the 1988 Meryl Streep movie 'A Cry In The Dark'). The band often played at the Bronze, for example during the foreign exchange trip in @{"Inca Mummy Girl" LINK "INCAMUMMYGIRL"}, and at the Valentine's Day dance in @{"Bewitched, Bothered and Bewildered" LINK "BEWITCHED"}.

He first entered the orbit of Buffy and her friends when a mysterious computer company picked him and Willow as potential employees, during the school's career fair in @{"What's My Line - Part 1" LINK "WHATSMYLINE1"}. Willow and Oz became friends, their relationship slowly becoming more intense (even though Willow still harboured feelings for Xander). Oz soon graduated to a fully-fledged member of Buffy's team, often supplying transport as well as pithy comments. After knocking about with Buffy and Willow for a while, Oz discovered that, like several members of his family, he was a werewolf! Every full moon, Oz had to be locked into a cage in the library, so that he couldn't harm himself, or other people.

Oz leaves town in @{"Wild At Heart" LINK "WILDATHEART"} after an encounter with Veruca, a female wearwolf, and the subsequent chaos makes him re-evaluate the danger he is to the gang and especially Willow. He returns in @{"New Moon Rising" LINK "NEWMOONRISING"} with his wearwolf side under control, to find Willow is now with Tara, and he takes off again, this time forever.

@{b}Goto:@{ub}   @{" String Search " SYSTEM "newcli WINDOW=CON:20/20/400//Buffy from Buffy.guide.cli"}@{"?" LINK "SEARCHREADME"}  @{" Major Events " LINK "EVENTS"}  @{" Characters " LINK "CHARACTERPROFILES"}  @{" Vocabulary " LINK "VAMPVOC"}  @{" Main Page " LINK "MAIN"}
@endnode

