@node "ABOUTQUENTIN" "Buffy.guide: About Quentin"

@{b}Quentin Travers@{ub}
(Harris Yulin)

Quentin has appeared twice, in @{"Helpless" LINK "HELPLESS"} (1999) and in @{"Checkpoint" LINK "CHECKPOINT"}, (2001).

Quentin is one of the most influential members of the Watcher's Council. On Buffy's eighteenth bithday, he subjects her to a test called the Cruciamentum, where the Slayer is disabled and locked away with a vampire to see if she can kill him using her brains rather than her brawn (see @{"Helpless" LINK "HELPLESS"}.) After approving the Slayer's skills he accuses Giles of being too emotionally close to his Slayer and fires him. Two years later, he witholds vital information about Glory while putting Giles and Buffy under review. Buffy soon realises she's actually the one in the position to call the shots since the information is useless to the Council without the Slayer's co-operation. Giles is re-instated as her watcher and the Council hands the information on Glory over.

@{b}Goto:@{ub}   @{" String Search " SYSTEM "newcli WINDOW=CON:20/20/400//Buffy from Buffy.guide.cli"}@{"?" LINK "SEARCHREADME"}  @{" Major Events " LINK "EVENTS"}  @{" Characters " LINK "CHARACTERPROFILES"}  @{" Vocabulary " LINK "VAMPVOC"}  @{" Main Page " LINK "MAIN"}
@endnode

@node "ABOUTRILEY" "Buffy.guide: About Riley"

@{b}Riley Finn@{ub}
(Marc Blucas)

2000 - 2001

Riley first encountered Buffy as a T.A. in Buffy's Psychology class, ###todo

Marc Blucas has had the rare opportunity to come within reach of two lifelong dreams: playing professional basketball and achieving Hollywood stardom with feature film roles and a recurring role as Buffy's (Sarah Michelle Gellar) new beau during season four on "Buffy the Vampire Slayer."

Born and raised in a small Pennsylvania town, Blucas' storybook childhood was centered on his talent for playing basketball, a gift that brought his high school team two state championships and earned him a scholarship to Wake Forest University. An Academic All-American and starter on the Division I team, Blucas graduated with a degree in business and communications.

After playing professionally for a year overseas, he left his hoop dreams behind and turned his focus to acting. Yet, it was his prowess on the basketball court that landed his first acting role, starring with Whoopi Goldberg in the sports-themed feature film "Eddie."

In the big-screen drama "Pleasantville," he landed a role as a high school basketball player from an open call audition. His experience on the court also came in handy as he was hired as a technical advisor on the film, casting the other players, consulting on the sports dialogue and choreographing the game scenes. He most recently appeared in the independent comedy "Mating Habits of the Earthbound Human" and the thriller "House on Haunted Hill."

On television, Blucas has starred in several television movies, including "The Jim Valvano Story" about the famous basketball coach for which he also served a technical advisor for the game scenes, and "Inflammable" with Kris Kristofferson. He also appeared opposite Jerry O'Connell in the miniseries "The 60's" and guest-starred on "Arli$$" and MTV's "Undressed."

When not working, Blucas spends his free time as a referee for a youth basketball league in Los Angeles.

@{b}Goto:@{ub}   @{" String Search " SYSTEM "newcli WINDOW=CON:20/20/400//Buffy from Buffy.guide.cli"}@{"?" LINK "SEARCHREADME"}  @{" Major Events " LINK "EVENTS"}  @{" Characters " LINK "CHARACTERPROFILES"}  @{" Vocabulary " LINK "VAMPVOC"}  @{" Main Page " LINK "MAIN"}
@endnode

