@node "BUFFYMARATHON" "Buffy.guide: Buffy Marathon"

@{b}Buffy The Vampire Slayer Guide - Buffy Marathon@{ub}

A Buffy marathon? That means, watching the entire existing series back-to-back? Oh yes, of course it @{i}sounds @{ui} insane. The series has clocked up approximately 5,240 minutes of action - just over 87 hours. That's more than three and a half days straight viewing. Why would anyone in their right minds do such a thing?

Well it's what I plan to do at some point in the near future. I've noticed what an immersive experience it can be to watch for more than a couple of hours, so in the spirit of general insanity, I'm going to attempt to watch all 87 hours of Buffy action in one sitting, and document it here for you! So, will I go insane? Decide I never want to watch Buffy ever again? Will I even make it through it all? Only time will tell... More on this experiment as soon as it happens! Need... more... coffee...

@{b}Goto:@{ub}   @{" String Search " SYSTEM "newcli WINDOW=CON:20/20/400//Buffy from Buffy.guide.cli"}@{"?" LINK "SEARCHREADME"}  @{" Major Events " LINK "EVENTS"}  @{" Characters " LINK "CHARACTERPROFILES"}  @{" Vocabulary " LINK "VAMPVOC"}  @{" Main Page " LINK "MAIN"}
@endnode

@node "VAMPVOC" "Buffy.guide: Vamp Vocabulary"

@{b}Buffy The Vampire Slayer Guide - Vamp Vocabulary@{ub}

Heard a word and not sure what you heard? Read on...


  @{b}A@{ub}

@{b}Astral Projection@{ub} (noun)
The theory that while one sleeps one has another (astral) body that can travel through time and space.

  @{b}B@{ub}

@{b}Binding Field@{ub} (noun)
A field of magical energy that surrounds the subject of the spell and puts them in a type of stasis.

@{b}Buff@{ub} (adjective)
Attractive, sexy.
"You think he's buff?" (Willow)
"He's a very attractive man! How come that never came up?" (Xander, @{"Teacher's Pet" LINK "TEACHERSPET"})

  @{b}C@{ub}

  @{b}D@{ub}

@{b}Dagon Sphere@{ub} (noun)
A glowing sphere, the purpose of which is to ward off @{"Glory" LINK "ABOUTGLORY"}.

  @{b}E@{ub}

  @{b}F@{ub}

@{b}Feeding@{ub} (noun)
Drinking blood; a vampire's only means for survival. Yummy!

  @{b}G@{ub}

  @{b}H@{ub}

@{b}Harvest@{ub} (noun)
A night once in a century when a Master Vampire can draw power from one of his minions while it feeds.

@{b}Hitchhiker@{ub} (noun)
A demon who observes a being or entity moving between dimensions or reality planes, and tags along for the ride.

@{b}Host@{ub} (noun)
The person off whom the vampire feeds.

@{b}Hottie@{ub} (noun)
Sexy person.
"That's right, I saw her. Pretty much a hottie!" (Xander, @{"Welcome to the Hellmouth" LINK "WELCOMETOHELLMOUTH"})

@{b}Huh@{ub} (interjection)
"I think I speak for everyone here when I say, 'Huh?'" (Buffy, @{"Invisible Girl" LINK "INVISIBLEGIRL"}

  @{b}I@{ub}

  @{b}J@{ub}

@{b}Justice Demon@{ub} (noun)
See Vengeance Demon.

  @{b}K@{ub}

  @{b}L@{ub}

@{b}Lackey@{ub}
See Minion.

@{b}Lethe's Bramble@{ub} (noun)
A key ingredient in spells involving mind-control or memory alteration.

  @{b}M@{ub}

@{b}Master@{ub} (noun)
The most powerful of vampires, capable of destroying the Earth.

@{b}Maxi-wig@{ub} (noun)
Variant on 'Wiggins'
"It's Angel, which automatically equals maxi-wig. (Buffy, @{"Surprise" LINK "SURPRISE"})

@{b}Minion@{ub} (noun)
A follower of any master vampire.

@{b}Minionator@{ub} (noun)
A corruption of the word minion, pioneered by Harmony.

  @{b}N@{ub}

  @{b}O@{ub}

###todo - orb of thesulah, other orbs!!!

  @{b}P@{ub}

  @{b}Q@{ub}

  @{b}R@{ub}

  @{b}S@{ub}

@{b}Scooby Gang@{ub} (noun)
Originally the gang in the US cartoon 'Scooby Doo', now used by Buffy's friends to describe themselves.
"You wanna be a  member of the Scooby Gang, you gotta be willing to be inconvenienced now and then." (Xander, @{"What's My Line - Part One" LINK "WHATSMYLINE1"}).

@{b}Sire@{ub}
When a vampire is made, the vampire who makes the new vampire, is the new vampire's sire. Say that when you're drunk!

@{b}Slayer@{ub} (noun)
A girl born once every generation with the strength and skill to hunt vampires, find them where they gather and stop the spread of their evil and the swell of their numbers. Our favourite slayer is @{"Buffy" LINK "ABOUTBUFFY"}, of course, but so far we've also met Kendra, Faith, and the nameless, mysterious First Slayer.

@{b}Slayerette@{ub} (noun)
Term used by Buffy's friends, denoting that they help in her fight against evil.
"Yeah! You're the Slayer, and we're, like, the Slayerettes!" (Willow, @{"The Witch" LINK "THEWITCH"}).

@{b}So@{ub} (adverb)
Used to mean really, extremely, totally.
"Oh! Great. I'm so the net girl." (Willow, @{"Lie to Me" LINK "LIETOME"})

  @{b}T@{ub}

  @{b}U@{ub}

  @{b}V@{ub}

@{b}Vamp@{ub} (noun)
Short for 'vampire'.

@{b}Vampire@{ub} (noun)
Demonic creatures who live off the blood of humans; a vampire appears to be a normal person until the feed is upon them - only then do they reveal their true demonic visage.

@{b}Vengeance Demon@{ub} (noun)
###todo Halfrek, anyanka

@{b}Vessel@{ub} (noun)
A minion, bearing a three-pointed symbol, which can give the Master Vampire power by feeding. The first Buffy and the gang encounter is Luke, from @{"Welcome to the Hellmouth" LINK "WELCOMETOHELLMOUTH"}.

  @{b}W@{ub}

@{b}Warlock@{ub} (noun)
A male practicer of witchcraft.

@{b}Watcher@{ub} (noun)
Person who finds the Slayer and leads her on her path; it is his destiny to guide the Slayer. Buffy's watcher is @{"Giles" LINK "ABOUTGILES"}.

@{b}Wiccan@{ub} (noun)
The more politically-correct term for a witch or practicer of modern witchcraft.

@{b}Wigged@{ub} (adjective)
"I think she's just so wigged at hitting on one of my friends that she's
repressing (Buffy, @{"Bewitched, Bothered and Bewildered" LINK "BEWITCHED"}).
"She's extra wigged this time... I guess, 'cause of her dreams." (Willow, @{"Innocence" LINK "INNOCENCE"}).

@{b}Wiggins@{ub} (noun)
Experience of fear, sensation that something is uncanny or freaky.
"Now I'm having a wiggins." (Xander, @{"Innocence" LINK "INNOCENCE"}).

@{b}Wiggy@{ub} (adjective)
Scared, or freaked out by something
"She was wiggy about the seal from minute one. (Buffy, @{"Inca Mummy Girl" LINK "INCAMUMMYGIRL"}).

  @{b}X@{ub}

  @{b}Y@{ub}

@{b}Yadda@{ub} (interjection)
Blah, nonesense.
"Prophecy, Anointed One, yadda, yadda, yadda..." (Buffy, @{"Never Kill a Boy on the First Date" LINK "NEVERKILLABOY"})

  @{b}Z@{ub}

