@node "SEARCHREADME" "Buffy.guide: BuffyGuideSearch readme"

@{b}Buffy The Vampire Slayer Guide - BuffyGuideSearch readme@{ub}

This readme file, and source for Matthew's search tool are included in the archive.

/* -----------------------------------------------------------
  @{b}BuffyGuideSearch.txt@{ub} 1.02 (24.05.2000)

  Documentation for the Buffy Guide Search

  (C) Copyright 2000 Matthew J Fletcher - All Rights Reserved.
  amimjf@connectfree.co.uk - www.amimjf.connectfree.co.uk
 ------------------------------------------------------------ */


@{b}Introduction@{ub}

This program was created to be used in conjunction with Chris Sheffield's Buffy.guide, a truly outstanding collection of Buffy info. Anyway various diffrent methods were used to try and get a decent search engine into the guide, using LSAGS and Chris's own custom ARexx code, however none of these really worked well, so I wrote a better version.


@{b}Usage@{ub}

This search engine is basically a cut down version of my regular expression engine, but the usage is much simpler. The best way to do it, is just to click on the search button in the guide. However it can be used seperately like this...

    cd BuffyGuide/
    BuffyGuideSearch Buffy.guide -s

where -s should be used if you want case sensitive search, or -h for help, or -v for verbose (lots of) output, or -d for the internal debug mode, which is probably best left alone, UNLESS you find a problem.


@{b}Requrements@{ub}

An Amiga, with a 020+ CPU and OS 3.x at least 20k of RAM (yes 20k). You will of course need Chris Sheffield's Buffy.guide, which can be found on Aminet.


@{b}Compilation@{ub}

This code compiles for Amiga gcc and Dice, and Borland C for Windows, it should work with others, but I can't test it. If you want to look at the code please feel free, if you want to compile it try...

Then type...

make -f makefile.amiga.gcc
or
dmake -f makefile.amiga.dice

and your program will appear in a few seconds.


@{b}Extras@{ub}

There is a port of the AmigaGuide system to windows (on Aminet), so you can re-compile this code to be used with Chris's guide on Windows systems if you really want to, you will have to make a project file yourself, but the sources have been coded so that support for BorlandC is in there.


@{b}Bugs@{ub}

My code does not have bugs... no, honest it doesn't... but the executable was compiled for 68020+ systems and so won't work on A500s.

If you find anything going weird, don't spam Chris 'cos its not his error. Mail me at the above address and I will see about it.

But please, please give me lots of info, search string, your system (RAM, processor, software versions, patches, background hacks etc). BUT most importantly a good description of the problem... If I can't reproduce it then I can't fix it.


@{b}Thanks@{ub}

Chris Sheffield, for creating the wonderfull Buffy guide...
Adam Dyer, for helping with a very annoying bug in the code...
Amiga Corp, for letting me have one of the developer boxes...
Buffy, for just being Buffy...

- Matthew J Fletcher

@{b}Goto:@{ub}   @{" String Search " SYSTEM "newcli WINDOW=CON:20/20/400//Buffy from Buffy.guide.cli"}@{"?" LINK "SEARCHREADME"}  @{" Major Events " LINK "EVENTS"}  @{" Characters " LINK "CHARACTERPROFILES"}  @{" Vocabulary " LINK "VAMPVOC"}  @{" Main Page " LINK "MAIN"}
@endnode

@node "GUIDEHISTORY" "Buffy.guide: Guide History"

@{b}Buffy The Vampire Slayer Guide - History@{ub}

History of this guide, in case you are interested. Probably not.


@{b}4.0@{ub}	Slapped myself round the face and said, You Can Do This...
	Season overviews added to main node. Too wordy?
	Totally removed Slayer's Circle. It sucked, anyone who wanted it subscribed :O)
	Attempted to make About node more concise.
	Character profiles moved to make it all tidier
	More standardized look for alphabetical lists
	Death row and character profiles combined.
	Added my own outlines from season 5 onwards
	Put buttons on bottom of (still not done) movie outline - knew something was wrong
	Added Goto buttons to bottom of character profiles
	Made Goto on Goto bars bold - that's good, dammit!
	Goto buttons make more sense - Index out, Characters in!
	Character profiles added: Joyce, Dawn, Tara, Clem, shitloads more
	Took 'P' prefix off some episode codes - they don't have the P on the credits
	Added some characters and demons to character profiles
	HTML version left to rot... it's sad really... wasn't it pretty? :O)
	Added insane Buffython thing

@{b}3.1@{ub}	Added Season 5 episode codes
	Altered 'Prophecy Girl' more info
	3.1 was the last version before my hiatus, and never made it to Aminet, IIRC.

@{b}3.0@{ub}	Added Slayer's Circle #61, Vol 5/#1, 5/#2
	Added 6 new episodes from Season 5
	Fixed some screwed-up links and loads of other problems.
	Added Trivia sections to 'The Witch' and 'The Pack'
	Added BBC info for 'The Freshman', 'Living Conditions',  'Harsh Light...', 'Fear...'
	Updated guide information page
	Updated 'Anne' More Information
	Slayer's Circle 'amputated' and in seperate file

@{b}2.2@{ub}	Added 'I Will Remember You' mini-synopsis (from Angel, but very Buffy-relevant)
	Added Slayer's Circle #58, #59, #60, Special Announcement
	Added BBC info for 'Choices', 'The Prom', 'Graduation Day'
	Added Ant's pilot episode synopsis
	Fixed two links on the 'About' page to Death Row, thanks to Ant
	Added Premiere Magazine article about Sarah

@{b}2.1@{ub}	Added BBC info for episodes up to 3ABB18
	Added Chris's Notes section to most recent episodes
	Added missing capital letters to one or two names (Wow, Earth-shattering!)
	View Last Search now opens seperate Multiview window (like after search)
	Added full descriptions for 'The Yoko Factor', 'Primeval' and 'Restless'
	Added Slayer's Circle #46 to #57 (still loads missing though, can u help?)
	Added some memorable/important quotes to top of episodes as an aide memoir
	Lots of extra info, quotes and details added to outlines
	Added section for the feature film, still under contruction...
	Split 'Welcome To The Hellmouth' properly

@{b}2.0@{ub}	Some annoying spelling mistakes removed
	Added TheWB teaser for 'Primeval' and 'Restless'
	Added BBC info for 'Band Candy' and 'Revelations'
	Added full descriptions for 'Where The Wild Things Are' and 'New Moon Rising'
	ARexx search replaced with Matthew J Fletcher's nice fast search tool
	Added Sarah Michelle Gellar MWB-icon (by MJF) and Buffy Newicon
	Added well-deserved thanks & credits to Matthew J Fletcher
	Added new 'Chris's Notes' section to some nodes
	More Slayer's Circle stuff added (#42, #43)
	HTML version now released!

@{b}1.6@{ub}	More Vamp Vocab examples
	Added BBC info for 'Beauty and the beasts' and 'Homecoming'
	Now with WordWrap! Saves much space too!
	3D bevels sacrificed
	XHelvetica/11 now used alongside XEN/9
	Added Zack Peacock credit to one part of the guide I forgot
	Slayer's Circle node added, SS #37, #38 and #41 included so far, more as and when available
	Death Row section added
	Ted, Spike, Drusilla, The Master moved to Death Row section
	Added information node on Riley + Anya
	More/updated information on main characters
	Character nodes now in order of appearance on main node
	Old (annoying) LSAGS search removed - now uses my ARexx search
	Added node begging for Pilot Episode information
	Added 'Problems' section on ABOUTGUIDE node, some FAQ questions shifted across

@{b}1.5@{ub}	Sarah Michelle Gellar's age corrected (it was 3 years out)
	Added character links to first episode
	Split 'Welcome to the Hellmouth' and 'The Harvest'
	Many spelling mistakes and typo's corrected
	Episode codes added for season one
	Loads more redundant info removed
	Weird spaces removed from line ends
	Most paragraphs seperated properly now
	All character outlines now have a separate node
	Put episode codes on main (contents) node
	New Major Events node, check it out!
	Nice 3D bevels added
	Added credit for Zack Peacock, for new season 4 outlines
	Added tiny instructions and my Amiga spec to ABOUTGUIDE node
	Goto bar added to bottom of all episode nodes
	5 new episodes added
	Added Faith node
	Fixed more apostrophe problems

@{b}1.4@{ub}	Search option added (LSAGS)
	Two new BBC reviews (Season 3, episodes 1 and 2)
	BuffySlayer.com and Buffy.guide FAQs merged
	History node added
	Many paragraph problems fixed
	FAQ edited due to AF closure (my plans were to include Buffy.guide on AFCD)
	Some cute little episdode links added
	Guide checked with BadLinks, only ONE link needed fixing! :-)
	font tag added to make sure line lengths are OK on normal or larger screen
	Added episode codes for seasons 2+3 (Why did I take them out in the first place?)
	First release, via Aminet and email to Jim from afb. Hi Jim! Shame the archive was corrupted

@{b}1.3@{ub}	Index added
	Entertaining Buffy.guide FAQ & About node added
	Season 3 completed
	Season 4 added, with codes
	Some redundant BBC info removed (stuff that was repeated in the official outlines)

@{b}1.2@{ub}	Seasons 1, 2 and much of 3 now covered
	Some of character information node 'Others' split into seperate nodes
	Vampire vocabulary section added
	BuffySlayer.com FAQ added
	More Buffy / Sarah Michelle Gellar info added (I know you like that!)
	Alan Hufana credited on main node for season 3 outlines

@{b}1.1@{ub}	'Others' character information node added
	Some official outlines added
	Still only Season 1 and 2

@{b}1.0@{ub}	First version.
	BBC stuff only!
	Only series 1 and 2 covered
	Simple Buffy and Angel character info nodes

